1
00:00:00,033 --> 00:00:01,232
This is Namhae.

2
00:00:01,233 --> 00:00:04,073
(The theme of this Namhae trip)

3
00:00:04,303 --> 00:00:06,403
(Holiday in Namhae)

4
00:00:06,773 --> 00:00:08,603
(A holiday on 2 Days 1 Night?)

5
00:00:08,773 --> 00:00:11,043
(Get in the car first.)

6
00:00:11,373 --> 00:00:14,683
(Only after Seon Ho gets in do they see...)

7
00:00:15,683 --> 00:00:17,353
(It's actually a working holiday in Namhae.)

8
00:00:18,683 --> 00:00:22,152
(They fish for cuttlefish.)

9
00:00:22,153 --> 00:00:23,223
No!

10
00:00:23,723 --> 00:00:27,323
(With Team Fishing's hard-earned cash,)

11
00:00:28,393 --> 00:00:30,232
(the others ride bikes and enjoy the sights.)

12
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:31,233
(Bike rent: 84 dollars)

13
00:00:32,033 --> 00:00:33,903
(They buy what they want to eat.)

14
00:00:34,363 --> 00:00:35,933
(Team Holiday has a great time.)

15
00:00:36,773 --> 00:00:40,473
(Two extreme experiences)

16
00:00:40,973 --> 00:00:43,673
(At last, they get a chance to avoid fishing.)

17
00:00:43,913 --> 00:00:45,783
(Joon must work twice in a row.)

18
00:00:45,883 --> 00:00:48,043
(Anchovy net-shaking)

19
00:00:48,783 --> 00:00:50,552
(While Team Fishing works,)

20
00:00:50,553 --> 00:00:55,283
(Team Holiday enjoys a leisurely meal.)

21
00:00:55,493 --> 00:00:58,693
(Will the rest of the working holiday be okay?)

22
00:00:59,523 --> 00:01:03,293
(2 Days 1 Night)

23
00:01:03,993 --> 00:01:05,632
Cameramen will get onto the boat first.

24
00:01:05,633 --> 00:01:07,103
Let's go.

25
00:01:08,203 --> 00:01:09,403
Can the cameramen...

26
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:13,173
(Where are we?)

27
00:01:13,443 --> 00:01:18,713
(Oh, right. We were working!)

28
00:01:18,943 --> 00:01:23,013
(Gathering their stuff)

29
00:01:23,353 --> 00:01:27,923
(They shuffle onto the boat.)

30
00:01:28,383 --> 00:01:30,723
Let's go back to work.

31
00:01:31,853 --> 00:01:35,323
(Anchovy fishing round 2)

32
00:01:37,093 --> 00:01:38,833
(Looking gloomy)

33
00:01:42,403 --> 00:01:46,603
(They're getting dragged to work in a haze.)

34
00:01:46,943 --> 00:01:48,813
- What time is it?
- It is...

35
00:01:49,843 --> 00:01:51,842
I haven't checked the time in so long.

36
00:01:51,843 --> 00:01:52,913
It's 3:30pm.

37
00:01:53,783 --> 00:01:56,753
This is a serious working holiday.

38
00:01:57,883 --> 00:02:00,523
- Come on up!
- Go on up!

39
00:02:02,853 --> 00:02:06,123
(Familiar with the drill, they get their gloves.)

40
00:02:06,623 --> 00:02:10,863
(Back to work)

41
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:15,703
(They join the rest of the workers.)

42
00:02:15,933 --> 00:02:17,002
Hello.

43
00:02:17,003 --> 00:02:19,473
(Welcome, young men!)

44
00:02:19,943 --> 00:02:21,242
- Like this?
- We climb over?

45
00:02:21,243 --> 00:02:25,372
(They shook anchovies from the net. What task awaits them now?)

46
00:02:25,373 --> 00:02:26,382
Let's do this.

47
00:02:26,383 --> 00:02:28,043
- Take this.
- Get moving!

48
00:02:28,083 --> 00:02:29,412
- Okay.
- Take this.

49
00:02:29,413 --> 00:02:31,483
Oh, we're moving these? Okay.

50
00:02:33,583 --> 00:02:34,922
Oh, we're moving these? Okay.

51
00:02:34,923 --> 00:02:36,423
Get moving. Hurry up.

52
00:02:37,553 --> 00:02:39,293
Watch out. It's heavy.

53
00:02:39,493 --> 00:02:40,863
Get to work.

54
00:02:42,363 --> 00:02:44,562
- Put it over there.
- Oh, we're stacking them?

55
00:02:44,563 --> 00:02:46,163
(Their next task)

56
00:02:46,733 --> 00:02:48,933
(The anchovies they shook free from the nets)

57
00:02:49,433 --> 00:02:56,243
(They collect the fish on the bottom of the boat...)

58
00:02:56,673 --> 00:02:59,112
(and stack them in crates...)

59
00:02:59,113 --> 00:03:02,283
(which is the last step of the fishing process.)

60
00:03:02,613 --> 00:03:03,952
It's very heavy.

61
00:03:03,953 --> 00:03:05,923
(It's very heavy!)

62
00:03:07,783 --> 00:03:11,393
(Each crate weighs over 30kg!)

63
00:03:13,193 --> 00:03:17,633
(The fishermen manage on their own.)

64
00:03:20,063 --> 00:03:24,673
(Only the strong survive here.)

65
00:03:25,203 --> 00:03:27,403
Everyone here must be so strong.

66
00:03:29,113 --> 00:03:31,812
(The work never ends.)

67
00:03:31,813 --> 00:03:34,412
Take a net and pour the fish into the crate.

68
00:03:34,413 --> 00:03:35,413
Okay.

69
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:38,452
(Anchovies fill the nets.)

70
00:03:38,453 --> 00:03:39,453
Pour them in.

71
00:03:41,023 --> 00:03:44,853
(Falling in)

72
00:03:45,393 --> 00:03:46,492
There's too many.

73
00:03:46,493 --> 00:03:47,992
(The crates overflow)

74
00:03:47,993 --> 00:03:49,033
Come on!

75
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:51,833
(Joon brings over a full crate.)

76
00:03:52,303 --> 00:03:55,103
(DinDin carries it away.)

77
00:03:55,733 --> 00:04:00,403
(Everyone must work as a team every step of the way.)

78
00:04:00,743 --> 00:04:03,212
(The work continues without a break.)

79
00:04:03,213 --> 00:04:04,373
Pick it up.

80
00:04:05,543 --> 00:04:06,613
(Yelling)

81
00:04:07,483 --> 00:04:08,683
(Yelling)

82
00:04:09,783 --> 00:04:11,953
Pick it up. You're doing it.

83
00:04:12,083 --> 00:04:13,283
Once more.

84
00:04:14,023 --> 00:04:15,153
There you go.

85
00:04:15,423 --> 00:04:17,353
- You're pretty good.
- He's not bad.

86
00:04:19,163 --> 00:04:20,263
Take it away.

87
00:04:20,793 --> 00:04:21,923
Good job.

88
00:04:24,993 --> 00:04:29,502
(DinDin hobbles away with the crate.)

89
00:04:29,503 --> 00:04:30,832
(Groaning)

90
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:32,443
- This is really heavy.
- Yes.

91
00:04:33,003 --> 00:04:34,973
Pick it up. There you go.

92
00:04:36,073 --> 00:04:39,943
(Grunting)

93
00:04:40,513 --> 00:04:42,752
(And endless river of tens of thousands of anchovies)

94
00:04:42,753 --> 00:04:44,483
- Pick it up.
- You're doing it.

95
00:04:45,413 --> 00:04:46,523
There you go.

96
00:04:46,753 --> 00:04:48,623
- You're pretty good.
- He's not bad.

97
00:04:51,023 --> 00:04:53,993
(It's hard work, but quietly, without giving up,)

98
00:04:56,063 --> 00:04:59,563
(Joon has been giving everything he does his all.)

99
00:05:00,663 --> 00:05:02,003
You're pretty good.

100
00:05:02,873 --> 00:05:04,832
Okay. Very good.

101
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:06,503
(The fishing doesn't end.)

102
00:05:07,273 --> 00:05:08,273
(Groaning)

103
00:05:11,073 --> 00:05:12,413
There's still a bit left.

104
00:05:12,483 --> 00:05:15,383
(The work continues.)

105
00:05:15,983 --> 00:05:21,053
(DinDin has a go at filling the crates.)

106
00:05:24,423 --> 00:05:28,263
(The fish on the floor go back into the net.)

107
00:05:30,393 --> 00:05:33,962
(The workers quietly give it their all.)

108
00:05:33,963 --> 00:05:35,033
That's it.

109
00:05:36,573 --> 00:05:38,172
Where to? Over here?

110
00:05:38,173 --> 00:05:40,543
(Joon moves the crates without stopping.)

111
00:05:40,903 --> 00:05:46,083
(There's no break on the workshop on the sea.)

112
00:05:46,283 --> 00:05:47,283
Hoist it up.

113
00:05:47,284 --> 00:05:49,012
(They move...)

114
00:05:49,013 --> 00:05:53,083
(and move more fish.)

115
00:05:53,653 --> 00:05:57,292
(After the last crate is taken away)

116
00:05:57,293 --> 00:05:58,393
Keep them in line.

117
00:05:58,693 --> 00:06:02,193
(The crates line one side of the boat.)

118
00:06:02,493 --> 00:06:03,862
(Impressed)

119
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:04,993
All that in a day?

120
00:06:06,303 --> 00:06:07,702
This is the least we ever caught.

121
00:06:07,703 --> 00:06:08,833
- For real?
- For real?

122
00:06:10,233 --> 00:06:11,503
This is the smallest catch?

123
00:06:12,443 --> 00:06:13,543
All that...

124
00:06:13,973 --> 00:06:15,503
That's 36, then 42.

125
00:06:15,913 --> 00:06:16,942
Forty-two crates.

126
00:06:16,943 --> 00:06:18,713
Each crate weighs 30kg.

127
00:06:18,843 --> 00:06:20,412
We caught tons of fish.

128
00:06:20,413 --> 00:06:21,413
We did.

129
00:06:22,213 --> 00:06:23,412
And that's the smallest catch?

130
00:06:23,413 --> 00:06:26,053
(They helped out and they still can't believe it.)

131
00:06:26,683 --> 00:06:29,023
- Good job!
- Well done!

132
00:06:29,523 --> 00:06:30,652
You have my total respect.

133
00:06:30,653 --> 00:06:31,953
(Anchovy fishing is over.)

134
00:06:32,193 --> 00:06:34,093
You two did so well.

135
00:06:34,293 --> 00:06:35,593
- You worked.
- Yes.

136
00:06:35,863 --> 00:06:37,733
- What...
- You get paid.

137
00:06:38,433 --> 00:06:39,663
How much could it be?

138
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:42,673
We can't pay you what the fishermen actually make.

139
00:06:42,803 --> 00:06:45,603
We considered your efforts, and decided the amount...

140
00:06:45,773 --> 00:06:46,973
should be 30 dollars per hour.

141
00:06:47,773 --> 00:06:49,003
How many hours did we work?

142
00:06:49,313 --> 00:06:52,983
You worked for 2 hours and made a total of 120 dollars.

143
00:06:53,743 --> 00:06:55,482
- So 120 dollars...
- We worked just 2 hours?

144
00:06:55,483 --> 00:06:57,052
(We only worked for two hours?)

145
00:06:57,053 --> 00:06:58,413
That's it?

146
00:06:58,953 --> 00:07:01,522
Buying bread was utter madness.

147
00:07:01,523 --> 00:07:02,553
Right?

148
00:07:02,793 --> 00:07:05,022
- The other guys will have...
- Eaten a lot.

149
00:07:05,023 --> 00:07:07,193
- They'll have spent some cash.
- Sure.

150
00:07:07,293 --> 00:07:08,992
- The bill...
- How much did they spend?

151
00:07:08,993 --> 00:07:10,562
The guys enjoying the trip...

152
00:07:10,563 --> 00:07:12,862
went to a camping ground nearby.

153
00:07:12,863 --> 00:07:14,102
- They went camping.
- And there...

154
00:07:14,103 --> 00:07:16,002
they rented a space.

155
00:07:16,003 --> 00:07:18,003
Why rent a space when they can eat on the ground?

156
00:07:18,403 --> 00:07:20,303
They spent 35 dollars to rent a space,

157
00:07:20,403 --> 00:07:22,203
and spent 66.7 dollars at the store.

158
00:07:23,073 --> 00:07:25,113
They spent over 66 dollars at a store?

159
00:07:25,243 --> 00:07:27,183
They ate over 70 dollars worth in the morning.

160
00:07:27,343 --> 00:07:29,282
- Yes.
- That's 130 dollars in food alone.

161
00:07:29,283 --> 00:07:31,953
What is there to eat in these stores?

162
00:07:31,983 --> 00:07:36,523
They also rented cooking utensils from the prop truck.

163
00:07:36,723 --> 00:07:38,222
That cost 25 dollars.

164
00:07:38,223 --> 00:07:39,423
(25 dollars to rent cooking utensils)

165
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:41,360
Jong Min couldn't sit on the ground,

166
00:07:41,393 --> 00:07:42,693
so he bought chairs for two dollars.

167
00:07:42,718 --> 00:07:43,718
Darn it.

168
00:07:44,093 --> 00:07:46,763
They spent additional 19.2 dollars at the cafeteria.

169
00:07:46,863 --> 00:07:48,463
Seon Ho spent two dollars on his ice cream.

170
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:50,103
So what's the total?

171
00:07:50,273 --> 00:07:52,372
- You guys are 135 dollars in debt.
- Come on.

172
00:07:52,373 --> 00:07:53,943
- Including the debt from before?
- Correct.

173
00:07:54,473 --> 00:07:55,542
I was so stupid.

174
00:07:55,543 --> 00:07:56,642
(They worked hard, but their debt only multiplied.)

175
00:07:56,643 --> 00:07:58,173
Imagine how I feel right now then.

176
00:07:59,143 --> 00:08:00,742
- I'm their mama bird.
- Earlier...

177
00:08:00,743 --> 00:08:01,843
Listen, Joon.

178
00:08:02,013 --> 00:08:04,712
You didn't see how easily they wasted money.

179
00:08:04,713 --> 00:08:05,713
- I didn't.
- I...

180
00:08:05,714 --> 00:08:06,852
Is it what I'm thinking?

181
00:08:06,853 --> 00:08:08,523
"Should we get it? Let's buy it." Is that it?

182
00:08:08,853 --> 00:08:11,392
- "They're going to earn money."
- Okay.

183
00:08:11,393 --> 00:08:13,193
"Let's buy some for the staff too." That's how it went.

184
00:08:13,523 --> 00:08:15,792
I doubt Se Yoon or Jong Min know what it's like here.

185
00:08:15,793 --> 00:08:17,533
But once you experience this... Right?

186
00:08:17,733 --> 00:08:21,132
The members who have been enjoying their trip are on their way here.

187
00:08:21,133 --> 00:08:22,363
- They're coming here?
- Yes.

188
00:08:22,703 --> 00:08:23,733
The car...

189
00:08:24,173 --> 00:08:26,003
It will be here in a few minutes. Just wait.

190
00:08:27,043 --> 00:08:29,003
He spent two dollars not to sit on the ground. That one is big.

191
00:08:29,477 --> 00:08:30,842
He just couldn't sit on the ground.

192
00:08:30,843 --> 00:08:32,713
(He finds this particular expense ridiculous.)

193
00:08:33,023 --> 00:08:34,623
We slept on the ground earlier.

194
00:08:36,183 --> 00:08:37,482
We slept out here.

195
00:08:37,483 --> 00:08:39,623
We lay down on the ground and slept there.

196
00:08:41,353 --> 00:08:44,923
(Their working holiday only makes them laugh in disbelief.)

197
00:08:45,493 --> 00:08:48,892
(Team Holiday's car pulls into the port at that time.)

198
00:08:48,893 --> 00:08:49,992
I see them here.

199
00:08:49,993 --> 00:08:52,433
- They're here?
- They're here. Isn't it them?

200
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:53,903
Yes, it's them.

201
00:08:55,463 --> 00:08:56,472
I think that's the car.

202
00:08:56,473 --> 00:08:57,473
(Joon spots Team Holiday.)

203
00:08:57,573 --> 00:08:58,973
The windshield wiper is on.

204
00:08:59,443 --> 00:09:00,503
Brother.

205
00:09:00,803 --> 00:09:02,073
- Brother.
- Hey, brother.

206
00:09:02,173 --> 00:09:03,512
- Give me a ride.
- Brother.

207
00:09:03,513 --> 00:09:04,843
Your face is wrecked.

208
00:09:05,573 --> 00:09:06,783
- Sit in the front.
- Let us hitchhike.

209
00:09:07,183 --> 00:09:08,812
- Brother.
- Sit in the front, guys.

210
00:09:08,813 --> 00:09:10,982
- Hello.
- Brothers.

211
00:09:10,983 --> 00:09:12,212
- Welcome.
- My gosh.

212
00:09:12,213 --> 00:09:13,222
- Sit in the front.
- Welcome.

213
00:09:13,223 --> 00:09:14,623
- Gosh, hello.
- You're late.

214
00:09:15,753 --> 00:09:16,793
My gosh.

215
00:09:17,553 --> 00:09:19,763
- You smell like anchovies.
- The smell is pretty pungent.

216
00:09:19,893 --> 00:09:21,223
- Really?
- You smell like the salty ocean.

217
00:09:21,763 --> 00:09:23,333
- Really? How bad is it?
- Yes.

218
00:09:24,193 --> 00:09:25,332
- Was it tough?
- Gosh, you stink.

219
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:29,133
Seriously. You can't whine about the smell right now.

220
00:09:29,433 --> 00:09:32,603
- Why?
- Because it was really tough.

221
00:09:32,703 --> 00:09:34,602
- Really?
- What happened to your face, Joon?

222
00:09:34,603 --> 00:09:36,612
- That's all anchovy poop.
- It's anchovy poop.

223
00:09:36,613 --> 00:09:38,043
- Anchovy poop?
- It's anchovy poop.

224
00:09:38,173 --> 00:09:40,042
The poop splashed on his face?

225
00:09:40,043 --> 00:09:43,913
Well, I'm also on another show where I work random part-time jobs.

226
00:09:44,153 --> 00:09:47,752
Of all part-time jobs I've done on that show, this one was...

227
00:09:47,753 --> 00:09:48,882
(It was the most excruciating job.)

228
00:09:48,883 --> 00:09:50,592
- the toughest job.
- Really?

229
00:09:50,593 --> 00:09:51,892
Let me give you an example.

230
00:09:51,893 --> 00:09:54,423
When we have to go hiking, we get angry and annoyed.

231
00:09:55,193 --> 00:09:56,962
This was beyond the annoyance we'd feel from hiking.

232
00:09:56,963 --> 00:09:58,563
It was beyond getting annoyed.

233
00:09:59,403 --> 00:10:00,602
- You just couldn't believe it?
- It was like...

234
00:10:00,603 --> 00:10:01,862
- There was nothing we could do.
- It humbled us.

235
00:10:01,863 --> 00:10:03,202
- It humbled us.
- Really?

236
00:10:03,203 --> 00:10:04,303
My gosh.

237
00:10:04,633 --> 00:10:05,803
- I know what you mean.
- Guys.

238
00:10:05,933 --> 00:10:07,903
- I can feel it.
- Do you want a cool drink?

239
00:10:08,303 --> 00:10:09,712
- I'm fine.
- We have a lot of money.

240
00:10:09,713 --> 00:10:10,772
- Let's get some.
- We have a lot of money.

241
00:10:10,773 --> 00:10:11,812
- Let's go over there.
- Okay.

242
00:10:11,813 --> 00:10:12,942
- How do we have a lot of money?
- But...

243
00:10:12,943 --> 00:10:14,882
- We're in debt.
- We're 135 dollars in debt.

244
00:10:14,883 --> 00:10:15,912
You guys worked hard.

245
00:10:15,913 --> 00:10:17,413
- I can buy a drink for you.
- Hey, let's get it.

246
00:10:17,513 --> 00:10:18,613
- Come on.
- Let's go.

247
00:10:18,853 --> 00:10:21,982
Seriously. Let me say something. I won't spend any money now.

248
00:10:21,983 --> 00:10:23,353
(I won't spend any money now.)

249
00:10:23,593 --> 00:10:25,022
- As if. I don't believe you.
- Gosh, right.

250
00:10:25,023 --> 00:10:26,162
I'm serious. I won't spend any money.

251
00:10:26,163 --> 00:10:27,393
He came to his senses.

252
00:10:27,693 --> 00:10:29,532
I almost cried earlier.

253
00:10:29,533 --> 00:10:32,132
- Thinking my actions in the past...
- He looked back on his life.

254
00:10:32,133 --> 00:10:33,202
How pretentious you were?

255
00:10:33,203 --> 00:10:37,403
(All the pretentious things I did earlier today...)

256
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:39,473
It humbled me endlessly.

257
00:10:39,803 --> 00:10:41,502
- He sounds like an adult now.
- Right.

258
00:10:41,503 --> 00:10:43,443
This job taught you a lesson.

259
00:10:43,573 --> 00:10:46,313
- Well, they're so different.
- They became different people.

260
00:10:46,883 --> 00:10:48,483
(Yawning)

261
00:10:48,583 --> 00:10:51,512
(Utterly fatigued after going through two jobs)

262
00:10:51,513 --> 00:10:53,182
I want to play games and do quizzes.

263
00:10:53,183 --> 00:10:55,382
(He's out of energy now.)

264
00:10:55,383 --> 00:10:57,592
- You want to use your brain now?
- Yes, I want to use my brain.

265
00:10:57,593 --> 00:10:58,723
- It was physically draining?
- Yes.

266
00:10:59,106 --> 00:11:00,476
It was so exhausting.

267
00:11:01,363 --> 00:11:03,162
I want to do quizzes on this show.

268
00:11:03,163 --> 00:11:04,262
You too, right?

269
00:11:04,263 --> 00:11:05,632
(After a long drive with the fatigued members...)

270
00:11:05,633 --> 00:11:06,862
- This is it?
- Yes.

271
00:11:06,863 --> 00:11:08,003
(Stop here.)

272
00:11:09,703 --> 00:11:13,203
(They're stopped in an outdoor parking lot by the staff.)

273
00:11:13,343 --> 00:11:15,143
It can't be the anchovies again. Right?

274
00:11:15,703 --> 00:11:17,573
All right. What about our meal today?

275
00:11:18,943 --> 00:11:20,513
Then why did we come out here, to begin with?

276
00:11:21,143 --> 00:11:22,243
We didn't know.

277
00:11:22,983 --> 00:11:25,182
(What's going on?)

278
00:11:25,183 --> 00:11:27,453
- We'll switch cars here.
- What's going on?

279
00:11:27,623 --> 00:11:28,822
- What?
- We're switching cars?

280
00:11:28,823 --> 00:11:29,993
Yes, we're switching cars.

281
00:11:30,493 --> 00:11:32,653
What's going on? I guess something's up.

282
00:11:33,463 --> 00:11:34,963
Let's stop here. We've done enough.

283
00:11:35,523 --> 00:11:37,062
- What's going on?
- Why are we switching cars?

284
00:11:37,063 --> 00:11:38,532
(An ominous feeling overwhelms them.)

285
00:11:38,533 --> 00:11:39,733
- Why are we switching cars?
- What?

286
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:41,363
You want us to get into this car?

287
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:42,533
- Why?
- This car?

288
00:11:42,534 --> 00:11:43,603
Yes. Please get in the car.

289
00:11:44,003 --> 00:11:45,173
Are we going to travel together?

290
00:11:47,343 --> 00:11:49,672
But why are we switching cars for no reason?

291
00:11:49,673 --> 00:11:51,313
What's going on? Why are we switching cars?

292
00:11:51,413 --> 00:11:53,843
- What's this? What's going on?
- What's going on?

293
00:11:54,343 --> 00:11:55,412
What is it?

294
00:11:55,413 --> 00:11:56,983
(Nervous)

295
00:11:57,253 --> 00:11:59,382
Let's get going, sir. Please turn right.

296
00:11:59,383 --> 00:12:00,553
Where are we going?

297
00:12:01,323 --> 00:12:04,353
Director, where are we going?

298
00:12:05,923 --> 00:12:07,163
The director isn't here.

299
00:12:07,293 --> 00:12:09,392
He's in the front. You just can't see him because he's short.

300
00:12:09,393 --> 00:12:10,462
- He's right here.
- Why did you say that?

301
00:12:10,463 --> 00:12:12,292
(The director is in the car.)

302
00:12:12,293 --> 00:12:13,832
- You're so mean.
- I really didn't see him.

303
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:16,002
Is it also like that when I sit in the front?

304
00:12:16,003 --> 00:12:17,533
- I can't see him at all.
- I can't see him at all.

305
00:12:18,503 --> 00:12:20,443
- Seriously. I can't see him at all.
- Hey, Hee Sung.

306
00:12:20,843 --> 00:12:22,812
- Where are we going?
- Where are we going?

307
00:12:22,813 --> 00:12:23,873
Where are we going?

308
00:12:24,673 --> 00:12:25,812
(Silent)

309
00:12:25,813 --> 00:12:27,313
Why did we suddenly switch cars?

310
00:12:27,983 --> 00:12:29,682
- This is scary.
- Fine. Don't say anything.

311
00:12:29,683 --> 00:12:30,683
He's not saying anything.

312
00:12:30,684 --> 00:12:32,653
I bet something serious is about to happen.

313
00:12:32,713 --> 00:12:34,652
- I bet he feels bad about it.
- Right.

314
00:12:34,653 --> 00:12:36,753
- He can't bring himself to tell us.
- We're here.

315
00:12:36,893 --> 00:12:38,152
- What? Where are we?
- It's right here.

316
00:12:38,153 --> 00:12:39,763
- What? We're already here?
- It's right here.

317
00:12:40,123 --> 00:12:41,692
- Why are we here?
- It's the campsite.

318
00:12:41,693 --> 00:12:42,693
- The campsite?
- It's the campsite again?

319
00:12:42,694 --> 00:12:44,132
- Is it the one we were at?
- No.

320
00:12:44,133 --> 00:12:45,392
No. It's not the one we were at.

321
00:12:45,393 --> 00:12:46,402
- What's going on?
- What?

322
00:12:46,403 --> 00:12:47,833
- Healing Leisure Campsite.
- Should we get out?

323
00:12:47,933 --> 00:12:49,032
- Yes. Only one of you...
- Here?

324
00:12:49,033 --> 00:12:50,132
will get out here.

325
00:12:50,133 --> 00:12:51,632
- Just one?
- What's going on?

326
00:12:51,633 --> 00:12:52,873
Who will get out here?

327
00:12:53,443 --> 00:12:56,312
- This is crazy.
- I'll get out.

328
00:12:56,313 --> 00:12:57,513
I didn't work today.

329
00:12:58,473 --> 00:12:59,982
- I'll get out.
- Wait.

330
00:12:59,983 --> 00:13:01,482
- Wait. This might be a good one.
- Hold on.

331
00:13:01,483 --> 00:13:02,882
- Don't try to be clever.
- Wait.

332
00:13:02,883 --> 00:13:04,012
- This is...
- Let's play rock-paper-scissors.

333
00:13:04,013 --> 00:13:05,252
- Let's play rock-paper-scissors.
- We'll play rock-paper-scissors.

334
00:13:05,253 --> 00:13:06,282
- Did you get that?
- No pressure then.

335
00:13:06,283 --> 00:13:07,283
- I got it.
- No other members...

336
00:13:07,284 --> 00:13:08,422
- I really got it.
- Okay.

337
00:13:08,423 --> 00:13:09,953
- Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

338
00:13:10,423 --> 00:13:11,923
- My gosh.
- Bye, Se Yoon.

339
00:13:12,193 --> 00:13:13,362
- You set this up, didn't you?
- This is crazy.

340
00:13:13,363 --> 00:13:14,962
- My gosh.
- The four of you will go?

341
00:13:14,963 --> 00:13:15,963
Let's bet everything.

342
00:13:15,964 --> 00:13:17,062
- Seriously.
- We didn't set it up.

343
00:13:17,063 --> 00:13:18,633
- Should we have a do-over?
- No.

344
00:13:18,933 --> 00:13:21,202
- Hey, seriously.
- You totally won this.

345
00:13:21,203 --> 00:13:22,562
- I'm serious.
- Okay.

346
00:13:22,563 --> 00:13:24,572
I want to work here. I'll get out here.

347
00:13:24,573 --> 00:13:26,132
- I bet this is a good one.
- No. You never know.

348
00:13:26,133 --> 00:13:27,802
- I'm getting a feeling...
- No. This is a good one.

349
00:13:27,803 --> 00:13:29,512
- Actually...
- this will be a good one.

350
00:13:29,513 --> 00:13:30,912
- Yes. Here's why.
- I bet this is a good one.

351
00:13:30,913 --> 00:13:32,942
Two of us were spared earlier from the labor.

352
00:13:32,943 --> 00:13:34,242
- Gosh.
- Two of us were spared.

353
00:13:34,243 --> 00:13:36,113
I'm getting a feeling that he's going to have it easy.

354
00:13:36,143 --> 00:13:37,753
Stop making them work!

355
00:13:38,183 --> 00:13:40,022
I'm going to work. I'll earn...

356
00:13:40,023 --> 00:13:42,383
(We're leaving.)

357
00:13:43,153 --> 00:13:45,692
(Just like they predicted, will he get to relax here?)

358
00:13:45,693 --> 00:13:46,863
- What's going on?
- Wait here.

359
00:13:47,023 --> 00:13:48,963
What could he do here? He'll just chill here.

360
00:13:49,093 --> 00:13:51,032
No. You never know.

361
00:13:51,033 --> 00:13:52,232
What if he asks us to get out again?

362
00:13:52,233 --> 00:13:53,362
- What do we do then?
- Right.

363
00:13:53,363 --> 00:13:54,402
- Let's play rock-paper-scissors.
- We'll play rock-paper-scissors.

364
00:13:54,403 --> 00:13:55,802
- Okay.
- Let's make it fair.

365
00:13:55,803 --> 00:13:57,273
- Let's not resent each other.
- Right.

366
00:13:57,573 --> 00:13:59,273
We have to accept the results. What else could we do?

367
00:14:00,373 --> 00:14:02,242
I'm getting scared. What are we going to do next?

368
00:14:02,243 --> 00:14:03,613
- We're at a rice paddy.
- What?

369
00:14:04,113 --> 00:14:05,772
- We'll work at a greenhouse next.
- Seriously.

370
00:14:05,773 --> 00:14:08,442
- Seriously? We'll work there?
- No. I bet there's a twist.

371
00:14:08,443 --> 00:14:09,583
- No, we'll work at a greenhouse.
- I'm getting a feeling.

372
00:14:09,713 --> 00:14:12,352
- I bet we'll work at a greenhouse.
- It's the greenhouse.

373
00:14:12,353 --> 00:14:13,853
Look. There are cameras here.

374
00:14:14,023 --> 00:14:15,553
- What are we doing here?
- We have to plant rice.

375
00:14:15,923 --> 00:14:17,252
What are we doing today?

376
00:14:17,253 --> 00:14:20,023
- One of you will get out here.
- No. You never know.

377
00:14:20,263 --> 00:14:22,563
- Who will get out?
- This is crazy.

378
00:14:22,663 --> 00:14:24,162
- Let nature take its course.
- Let nature take its course?

379
00:14:24,163 --> 00:14:25,292
- Yes.
- Rock...

380
00:14:25,293 --> 00:14:26,362
- Rock-paper...
- Wait.

381
00:14:26,363 --> 00:14:27,762
- The loser will get out?
- The loser will get out.

382
00:14:27,763 --> 00:14:29,233
- Rock-paper-scissors.
- Scissors.

383
00:14:29,363 --> 00:14:31,002
- Okay.
- I wonder what's going to happen.

384
00:14:31,003 --> 00:14:32,233
- I'll leave it up to fate.
- Fate.

385
00:14:32,603 --> 00:14:33,642
- There's nothing we can do.
- Good luck.

386
00:14:33,643 --> 00:14:34,742
- There's nothing we can do.
- Okay.

387
00:14:34,743 --> 00:14:36,372
Okay. There's nothing I can do. Go.

388
00:14:36,373 --> 00:14:38,142
People use machines to transplant rice seedlings these days.

389
00:14:38,143 --> 00:14:40,482
- Have fun.
- I doubt you'll do that.

390
00:14:40,483 --> 00:14:41,483
Okay.

391
00:14:41,743 --> 00:14:43,752
(Will DinDin end up working back to back?)

392
00:14:43,753 --> 00:14:44,753
(Disappointed)

393
00:14:44,754 --> 00:14:46,723
(His cameraman gets out with a disappointed sigh.)

394
00:14:46,853 --> 00:14:48,652
Why did you sigh when you get out?

395
00:14:48,653 --> 00:14:49,692
(Why did you sigh?)

396
00:14:49,693 --> 00:14:51,923
- Why did you sigh like that?
- What?

397
00:14:52,693 --> 00:14:55,123
No. It has to be better than anchovy net-shaking.

398
00:14:57,793 --> 00:15:01,203
(Waiting for an update in a pitiful pose)

399
00:15:01,403 --> 00:15:02,632
One person at the campsite.

400
00:15:02,633 --> 00:15:04,233
- The campsite. The rice paddy.
- One person at the rice paddy.

401
00:15:04,673 --> 00:15:06,502
- Then...
- The last one...

402
00:15:06,503 --> 00:15:07,673
Are we going to the mountain?

403
00:15:08,443 --> 00:15:10,012
I can't even guess right now.

404
00:15:10,013 --> 00:15:11,542
(I have no clue.)

405
00:15:11,543 --> 00:15:13,242
I think we're going to stop here.

406
00:15:13,243 --> 00:15:14,282
This is driving me crazy.

407
00:15:14,283 --> 00:15:15,642
(Their anxiety is deepening.)

408
00:15:15,643 --> 00:15:16,683
Seriously. This is crazy.

409
00:15:16,983 --> 00:15:20,183
We might have to work at all of these spots.

410
00:15:20,723 --> 00:15:22,453
One of you will get out here again.

411
00:15:22,993 --> 00:15:25,222
- Are we all going to get split up?
- I guess so.

412
00:15:25,223 --> 00:15:27,323
(The three of them got out at different spots.)

413
00:15:28,523 --> 00:15:30,133
You startled me. My gosh.

414
00:15:31,563 --> 00:15:33,833
- Let's stand here.
- I thought I was getting kidnapped.

415
00:15:37,073 --> 00:15:43,912
(A beautiful, tiny village in the Namhae countryside)

416
00:15:43,913 --> 00:15:46,943
(A beautiful, run-down village in the Namhae countryside)

417
00:15:47,783 --> 00:15:49,652
(The staff dropped off the members at random spots...)

418
00:15:49,653 --> 00:15:50,782
(Se Yoon, DinDin, Jong Min,)

419
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:52,182
(Joon, and Seon Ho)

420
00:15:52,183 --> 00:15:55,023
(around the village.)

421
00:15:55,153 --> 00:15:56,493
- Seon Ho.
- Yes.

422
00:15:56,923 --> 00:15:57,952
A while ago...

423
00:15:57,953 --> 00:16:00,762
Team Holiday's extravagant spending...

424
00:16:00,763 --> 00:16:02,623
left you guys 135 dollars in debt.

425
00:16:03,293 --> 00:16:06,063
All of you will work to pay off the debt.

426
00:16:06,433 --> 00:16:08,703
Here's the final task of the working holiday.

427
00:16:10,133 --> 00:16:11,373
This is the most representative crop of Namhae.

428
00:16:13,003 --> 00:16:14,343
You must harvest garlic scapes.

429
00:16:14,873 --> 00:16:16,342
(Until they can write off the debt)

430
00:16:16,343 --> 00:16:17,713
We must harvest garlic scapes?

431
00:16:17,943 --> 00:16:19,513
I see. All of us have to do it?

432
00:16:19,943 --> 00:16:20,983
Then...

433
00:16:21,513 --> 00:16:23,213
I did all three tasks.

434
00:16:23,713 --> 00:16:25,913
I never got to enjoy the holiday part of this trip.

435
00:16:26,383 --> 00:16:28,183
Darn it. Come on.

436
00:16:28,323 --> 00:16:29,452
(Feeling dejected)

437
00:16:29,453 --> 00:16:30,693
This is the last one?

438
00:16:31,147 --> 00:16:32,386
There's no more?

439
00:16:33,193 --> 00:16:35,222
Now, I'll give you one last chance...

440
00:16:35,223 --> 00:16:36,862
to be exempted from the group task.

441
00:16:36,863 --> 00:16:38,033
I can get exempted?

442
00:16:38,563 --> 00:16:41,103
(From their locations...)

443
00:16:41,603 --> 00:16:44,133
Today's base camp is...

444
00:16:44,473 --> 00:16:45,872
within a 500m radius.

445
00:16:45,873 --> 00:16:47,243
(Base camp)

446
00:16:47,573 --> 00:16:48,973
Within seven minutes,

447
00:16:49,643 --> 00:16:52,073
if all of you can find and arrive at the base camp...

448
00:16:52,743 --> 00:16:54,642
All of your debt will be written off.

449
00:16:54,643 --> 00:16:55,643
Really?

450
00:16:56,013 --> 00:16:57,712
- But we have to walk there?
- Yes.

451
00:16:57,713 --> 00:16:59,013
(No cars will be provided.)

452
00:16:59,183 --> 00:17:01,052
Then can I call them?

453
00:17:01,053 --> 00:17:02,282
You're not allowed to use your phone.

454
00:17:02,283 --> 00:17:03,323
Then how can we find the base camp?

455
00:17:03,753 --> 00:17:06,322
That's why we'll provide you the map of the village as a hint.

456
00:17:06,323 --> 00:17:08,122
(The map of the village is provided as a hint.)

457
00:17:08,123 --> 00:17:10,192
(Base camp, Sinjeon Village Hall)

458
00:17:10,193 --> 00:17:11,493
What's Sinjeon Village Hall?

459
00:17:12,633 --> 00:17:13,732
How can I read this map?

460
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:14,802
I don't know where Sinjeon Village Hall is.

461
00:17:14,803 --> 00:17:16,303
You have to tell me where I am.

462
00:17:16,473 --> 00:17:18,733
Do you think I'm a shaman? How can I find it?

463
00:17:20,273 --> 00:17:21,942
I don't know where I am.

464
00:17:21,943 --> 00:17:23,972
(Finding out their current location is the first step.)

465
00:17:23,973 --> 00:17:25,142
If you fail...

466
00:17:25,143 --> 00:17:26,143
(Don't forget.)

467
00:17:26,144 --> 00:17:27,843
you will have to stay late to harvest garlic scapes.

468
00:17:29,343 --> 00:17:31,253
- It will take four hours.
- Okay.

469
00:17:33,183 --> 00:17:35,052
(Will they be able to find the base camp in 7 minutes?)

470
00:17:35,053 --> 00:17:36,623
All right. Let's begin.

471
00:17:36,793 --> 00:17:38,153
Go.

472
00:17:39,863 --> 00:17:41,993
I must know where I am first to find the base camp.

473
00:17:42,663 --> 00:17:44,593
(He's trying to find his location.)

474
00:17:45,233 --> 00:17:46,332
Where am I?

475
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:47,833
(But he doesn't have a clue.)

476
00:17:48,103 --> 00:17:50,033
Where am I? I see a village.

477
00:17:50,603 --> 00:17:52,473
The village must be over there...

478
00:17:52,603 --> 00:17:53,672
looking at the greenhouses.

479
00:17:53,673 --> 00:17:55,202
(Exuding major troublemaker vibes)

480
00:17:55,203 --> 00:17:56,273
My gosh. Seriously.

481
00:17:56,513 --> 00:17:58,642
I don't know where I am. I have a bad sense of direction.

482
00:17:58,643 --> 00:17:59,813
(Also exuding major troublemaker vibes)

483
00:17:59,983 --> 00:18:01,083
I have a bad sense of direction.

484
00:18:01,483 --> 00:18:02,583
That's the road.

485
00:18:03,553 --> 00:18:05,282
The campsite is over there. How can I get out of here?

486
00:18:05,283 --> 00:18:06,682
(No Sense of Direction has failed to find a way out.)

487
00:18:06,683 --> 00:18:07,706
Sir, how can I get out of here?

488
00:18:08,583 --> 00:18:09,922
Where am I now?

489
00:18:09,923 --> 00:18:11,253
(Joon is also lost.)

490
00:18:11,553 --> 00:18:12,393
Hold on.

491
00:18:13,323 --> 00:18:14,363
Wait.

492
00:18:15,723 --> 00:18:16,733
Wait.

493
00:18:19,963 --> 00:18:22,463
This is Namseo-daero. Wait, it's not shown here.

494
00:18:23,773 --> 00:18:25,032
(No matter how hard he stares at the map...)

495
00:18:25,033 --> 00:18:26,972
This is driving me crazy.

496
00:18:26,973 --> 00:18:28,003
(he hasn't the faintest clue.)

497
00:18:28,543 --> 00:18:31,373
(Becoming the 3rd possible troublemaker)

498
00:18:32,273 --> 00:18:34,983
(The three of them haven't left the drop-off spots.)

499
00:18:35,613 --> 00:18:38,153
(Meanwhile, DinDin...)

500
00:18:39,853 --> 00:18:43,593
(calmly checks the scenery against the map.)

501
00:18:44,153 --> 00:18:45,223
Wait.

502
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:51,663
I think it's that way.

503
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:54,732
(He runs with a sense of certainty.)

504
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:55,763
Seven minutes.

505
00:18:56,363 --> 00:18:59,873
(He runs quite a bit to get out of the rice paddy.)

506
00:19:00,543 --> 00:19:01,543
Excuse me!

507
00:19:02,843 --> 00:19:04,242
(The driver stops as DinDin calls out.)

508
00:19:04,243 --> 00:19:06,913
Do you know where Sinjeon Village Hall is?

509
00:19:07,183 --> 00:19:08,712
Where is Sinjeon Village Hall?

510
00:19:08,713 --> 00:19:09,742
It's up there.

511
00:19:09,743 --> 00:19:10,852
- Over there?
- Yes.

512
00:19:10,853 --> 00:19:12,413
- Thank you.
- Sure.

513
00:19:14,923 --> 00:19:16,122
(He stays on the same path after asking for directions.)

514
00:19:16,123 --> 00:19:17,923
You should go that way.

515
00:19:18,223 --> 00:19:19,553
- This way?
- There.

516
00:19:19,923 --> 00:19:21,063
Thank you.

517
00:19:22,063 --> 00:19:25,262
(Thanks to the kind driver, he takes the shortcut.)

518
00:19:25,263 --> 00:19:26,433
It's pretty far.

519
00:19:27,863 --> 00:19:28,903
"Seonjeon Village Hall."

520
00:19:29,003 --> 00:19:30,802
(Seon Ho starts running too.)

521
00:19:30,803 --> 00:19:32,173
Where's Seonjeon Village Hall?

522
00:19:34,703 --> 00:19:39,212
(He keeps on running, but he can't see anything.)

523
00:19:39,213 --> 00:19:41,242
- Two minutes have passed.
- No.

524
00:19:41,243 --> 00:19:43,043
(He spent 2 minutes to enter the village.)

525
00:19:43,453 --> 00:19:45,412
Ma'am, hello.

526
00:19:45,413 --> 00:19:47,323
- Can I ask you a question?
- Sure.

527
00:19:47,953 --> 00:19:49,452
I'm from the KBS show, 2 Days 1 Night.

528
00:19:49,453 --> 00:19:51,023
- Yes, I know.
- Okay.

529
00:19:51,223 --> 00:19:53,093
Where's Sinjeon Village Hall?

530
00:19:53,463 --> 00:19:54,862
The village hall is that way.

531
00:19:54,863 --> 00:19:56,322
- Will I see it if I go up this way?
- Yes.

532
00:19:56,323 --> 00:19:58,292
- Thank you.
- Sure.

533
00:19:58,293 --> 00:19:59,903
I know your face,

534
00:20:00,463 --> 00:20:02,063
- but I don't know your name.
- It's Seon Ho.

535
00:20:02,203 --> 00:20:03,832
- Seon Ho.
- Yes. Thank you.

536
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:04,873
(It's Yoo Seon Ho.)

537
00:20:05,333 --> 00:20:09,543
(He runs again after gathering important information.)

538
00:20:10,113 --> 00:20:11,342
Where's Sinjeon Village Hall?

539
00:20:11,343 --> 00:20:13,173
(DinDin and Seon Ho are running to their destination.)

540
00:20:13,543 --> 00:20:15,183
(Slow)

541
00:20:15,583 --> 00:20:17,653
I don't see any greenhouses.

542
00:20:18,383 --> 00:20:19,453
"The base camp."

543
00:20:20,153 --> 00:20:21,153
I'm in trouble.

544
00:20:21,154 --> 00:20:23,392
(He can at least grasp the situation he's in.)

545
00:20:23,393 --> 00:20:24,452
Should I ask them?

546
00:20:24,453 --> 00:20:26,193
Is there anyone inside?

547
00:20:26,623 --> 00:20:27,793
Is anyone here?

548
00:20:28,393 --> 00:20:29,422
Hello.

549
00:20:29,423 --> 00:20:30,932
(Becoming an introvert)

550
00:20:30,933 --> 00:20:32,232
- I...
- Where are you from?

551
00:20:32,233 --> 00:20:34,362
I'm from the KBS show. We're from Seoul.

552
00:20:34,363 --> 00:20:35,402
It's Jong Min.

553
00:20:35,403 --> 00:20:36,772
(Of course, I know Kim Jong Min.)

554
00:20:36,773 --> 00:20:39,873
I'm trying to get to this house from Sinjeon Village Hall.

555
00:20:40,303 --> 00:20:42,173
Your base camp is right here.

556
00:20:42,443 --> 00:20:44,412
- The base camp is right here?
- It's up there.

557
00:20:44,413 --> 00:20:45,943
- That house? The village hall...
- No.

558
00:20:46,273 --> 00:20:48,182
- I see. No, it's not here.
- Over there...

559
00:20:48,183 --> 00:20:50,052
- Isn't it across the street?
- No.

560
00:20:50,053 --> 00:20:52,013
Can someone find where Sinjeon Village Hall is?

561
00:20:52,413 --> 00:20:54,153
Is it over there? Wait, no. That's...

562
00:20:54,283 --> 00:20:55,923
At the intersection from Sinjeon Village Hall,

563
00:20:56,123 --> 00:20:58,193
I just have to go up this way. Then it should be there.

564
00:20:58,323 --> 00:20:59,652
Where's Sinjeon Village Hall? There?

565
00:20:59,653 --> 00:21:02,692
It's over there. Do you see the storage-looking building?

566
00:21:02,693 --> 00:21:03,693
Yes.

567
00:21:04,233 --> 00:21:07,462
It's right there. At the end of the road,

568
00:21:07,463 --> 00:21:08,762
- Okay.
- you'll see the village hall.

569
00:21:08,763 --> 00:21:09,972
- Over there?
- Yes.

570
00:21:09,973 --> 00:21:11,202
(It's obvious he didn't get that.)

571
00:21:11,203 --> 00:21:12,903
Okay. I'll try to find it.

572
00:21:13,303 --> 00:21:14,543
- So...
- Yes.

573
00:21:14,743 --> 00:21:16,002
(He figures out that Jong Min didn't understand it.)

574
00:21:16,003 --> 00:21:17,713
I don't have that much time left.

575
00:21:18,513 --> 00:21:19,643
- Let's see.
- Okay.

576
00:21:19,913 --> 00:21:21,342
- Take that path.
- Okay.

577
00:21:21,343 --> 00:21:23,552
Then you'll come to another path.

578
00:21:23,553 --> 00:21:25,852
I see. Okay, sir. I'll get going.

579
00:21:25,853 --> 00:21:27,353
It's right there.

580
00:21:27,483 --> 00:21:28,952
Okay, sir. Thank you.

581
00:21:28,953 --> 00:21:30,093
Should I go this way?

582
00:21:30,993 --> 00:21:32,322
He told me to go to the main road.

583
00:21:32,323 --> 00:21:34,693
- You're the one who asked him.
- Okay.

584
00:21:34,893 --> 00:21:36,023
I didn't get that.

585
00:21:36,793 --> 00:21:38,693
He said he could see it from here.

586
00:21:39,193 --> 00:21:40,863
He said it was on the other side.

587
00:21:44,703 --> 00:21:45,733
Am I wrong?

588
00:21:46,773 --> 00:21:48,103
No, this isn't the right direction.

589
00:21:48,843 --> 00:21:49,973
Is it that way?

590
00:21:50,943 --> 00:21:53,313
Hold on. Am I going into the right direction?

591
00:21:54,283 --> 00:21:57,083
(He manages to enter the village.)

592
00:21:57,483 --> 00:21:59,183
Is Jong Min here too?

593
00:21:59,813 --> 00:22:01,983
It's you, Se Yoon. You look the same in person.

594
00:22:02,423 --> 00:22:04,323
(Wait. This lady...)

595
00:22:04,953 --> 00:22:07,422
(She met Seon Ho about 1 minute ago.)

596
00:22:07,423 --> 00:22:09,162
- The village hall is that way.
- Will I see it if I go up this way?

597
00:22:09,163 --> 00:22:10,633
(She kindly told Seon Ho the direction.)

598
00:22:10,833 --> 00:22:12,992
Ma'am, do you know how to read maps?

599
00:22:12,993 --> 00:22:14,163
I'm bad with directions.

600
00:22:14,303 --> 00:22:16,933
Sinjeon Village Hall is right here. But I need to get to this house.

601
00:22:17,103 --> 00:22:19,303
- You can keep going up.
- Thank you.

602
00:22:21,343 --> 00:22:23,473
(He goes up straight just like she told him.)

603
00:22:24,913 --> 00:22:26,043
He's running.

604
00:22:29,543 --> 00:22:30,612
DinDin!

605
00:22:30,613 --> 00:22:32,113
(He spots DinDin who's running from a distance.)

606
00:22:32,753 --> 00:22:33,783
DinDin!

607
00:22:34,443 --> 00:22:35,307
DinDin!

608
00:22:36,023 --> 00:22:37,323
It's this way, Se Yoon!

609
00:22:38,253 --> 00:22:39,121
This way!

610
00:22:39,293 --> 00:22:42,263
(DinDin: It's this way, Se Yoon! This way!)

611
00:22:42,863 --> 00:22:43,933
It's over there?

612
00:22:45,493 --> 00:22:47,262
Okay. My gosh. This is it.

613
00:22:47,263 --> 00:22:48,303
(He finally figures out the correct direction.)

614
00:22:49,203 --> 00:22:51,933
(The two of them are running in the same direction.)

615
00:22:52,603 --> 00:22:55,343
(Gasping for air)

616
00:22:56,703 --> 00:22:58,612
(It sounds like he's about to run out of breath.)

617
00:22:58,613 --> 00:23:00,942
(He stops running in the end.)

618
00:23:00,943 --> 00:23:02,512
I ate too much ramyeon. I can't run.

619
00:23:02,513 --> 00:23:04,013
(Unable to run after eating too much ramyeon)

620
00:23:04,353 --> 00:23:05,382
(Remaining time)

621
00:23:05,383 --> 00:23:08,123
(Number of arrivals: 0)

622
00:23:10,053 --> 00:23:11,122
Joon arrived.

623
00:23:11,123 --> 00:23:12,393
(Joon has arrived?)

624
00:23:12,893 --> 00:23:16,423
(Joon was lost. How did he find the base camp?)

625
00:23:16,993 --> 00:23:18,432
Yes. I should take the main road.

626
00:23:18,433 --> 00:23:20,433
(He was lost for a while and kept running to the main road.)

627
00:23:20,863 --> 00:23:22,262
(He sprinted at full speed...)

628
00:23:22,263 --> 00:23:23,602
(as the anchovy poop fluttered away on his face.)

629
00:23:23,603 --> 00:23:24,603
(Breathing hard)

630
00:23:29,143 --> 00:23:32,542
It's Sinjeon Village Hall. I found Sinjeon Village Hall.

631
00:23:32,543 --> 00:23:33,982
(He stumbled across Sinjeon Village Hall.)

632
00:23:33,983 --> 00:23:35,113
I have to turn left here.

633
00:23:35,543 --> 00:23:39,553
(Actually, it was the closest from Joon's drop-off point.)

634
00:23:40,053 --> 00:23:41,082
I have to keep going straight.

635
00:23:41,083 --> 00:23:42,182
(And he kept going straight.)

636
00:23:42,183 --> 00:23:43,223
Keep going straight.

637
00:23:44,123 --> 00:23:46,253
(Joon was the 1st one to arrive in 4 minutes and 20 seconds.)

638
00:23:46,823 --> 00:23:48,493
- I'm smart, aren't I?
- Yes.

639
00:23:49,023 --> 00:23:50,092
I'm smart.

640
00:23:50,093 --> 00:23:51,333
(He got lucky with the drop-off point.)

641
00:23:51,693 --> 00:23:52,733
It's here!

642
00:23:53,333 --> 00:23:54,363
Over here!

643
00:23:54,763 --> 00:23:57,102
Joon! It must be here.

644
00:23:57,103 --> 00:23:58,832
(Seon Ho happened to be around.)

645
00:23:58,833 --> 00:24:01,202
You need a cameraman with you. Wait up.

646
00:24:01,203 --> 00:24:02,673
(He ditches the staff member and sprints.)

647
00:24:03,173 --> 00:24:04,242
Seon Ho has arrived too.

648
00:24:04,243 --> 00:24:05,473
(Seon Ho arrives at the base camp in 4 minutes and 50 seconds.)

649
00:24:05,973 --> 00:24:09,012
(Why is he suddenly going to the terrace?)

650
00:24:09,013 --> 00:24:10,612
It's over here!

651
00:24:10,613 --> 00:24:12,652
(Joon is planning to gather the members by shouting.)

652
00:24:12,653 --> 00:24:13,723
Run!

653
00:24:15,923 --> 00:24:18,223
It's over here! Run!

654
00:24:19,223 --> 00:24:20,293
It's over there.

655
00:24:25,493 --> 00:24:27,432
(DinDin hears his voice and runs over.)

656
00:24:27,433 --> 00:24:28,963
You're Im Cheol!

657
00:24:29,533 --> 00:24:30,973
- Where is it?
- Right here.

658
00:24:31,233 --> 00:24:32,732
Keep going Joon!

659
00:24:32,733 --> 00:24:34,043
No. I mean...

660
00:24:35,473 --> 00:24:38,643
(He had a nice plan, but couldn't speak clearly.)

661
00:24:38,843 --> 00:24:40,042
Keep going straight!

662
00:24:40,043 --> 00:24:41,612
(That's what he wanted to say.)

663
00:24:41,613 --> 00:24:42,813
Just keep going straight.

664
00:24:43,883 --> 00:24:45,012
The others should be here now.

665
00:24:45,013 --> 00:24:46,883
(DinDin arrives with 1 minute and 48 seconds to spare.)

666
00:24:47,423 --> 00:24:48,583
Jong Min...

667
00:24:49,623 --> 00:24:50,853
Why can't I see him at all?

668
00:24:51,053 --> 00:24:52,853
I can't see them!

669
00:24:53,863 --> 00:24:57,232
(Time is ticking away.)

670
00:24:57,233 --> 00:24:58,332
(Where on earth are they?)

671
00:24:58,333 --> 00:25:00,093
Am I going in the right way?

672
00:25:00,509 --> 00:25:02,309
Moon Se Yoon!

673
00:25:02,579 --> 00:25:03,619
It's over there.

674
00:25:04,258 --> 00:25:05,358
- Run!
- Okay.

675
00:25:06,789 --> 00:25:08,018
Run!

676
00:25:08,019 --> 00:25:09,759
(Se Yoon, it's over here!)

677
00:25:09,919 --> 00:25:11,088
We have a minute left!

678
00:25:11,089 --> 00:25:13,589
- One minute!
- There's one minute left!

679
00:25:13,759 --> 00:25:15,528
My gosh. Is it this way?

680
00:25:15,529 --> 00:25:17,329
(Jong Min still has no idea where he's going.)

681
00:25:19,129 --> 00:25:20,599
Over here!

682
00:25:21,099 --> 00:25:22,169
I can hear his voice.

683
00:25:22,569 --> 00:25:24,139
- 2 Days...
- Run!

684
00:25:24,869 --> 00:25:25,869
(He finally figures out the direction.)

685
00:25:25,870 --> 00:25:27,469
- 1 Night!
- It's over there.

686
00:25:29,239 --> 00:25:31,638
(To avoid working on the field...)

687
00:25:31,639 --> 00:25:33,849
We're not a running crew. Why are we running so much?

688
00:25:34,349 --> 00:25:36,219
(the older members keep running without a break.)

689
00:25:36,479 --> 00:25:38,578
It must be over there. I just have to keep running.

690
00:25:38,579 --> 00:25:40,448
(The two of them are getting close to the base camp.)

691
00:25:40,449 --> 00:25:41,589
One minute.

692
00:25:42,349 --> 00:25:44,159
- It's over here!
- Where?

693
00:25:45,059 --> 00:25:46,959
- They're both coming.
- They're both coming.

694
00:25:47,889 --> 00:25:49,159
- Run!
- They're over there.

695
00:25:49,699 --> 00:25:50,829
They're waving at me.

696
00:25:51,099 --> 00:25:53,498
- We have a minute left.
- One minute!

697
00:25:53,499 --> 00:25:54,699
We have a minute left.

698
00:25:55,669 --> 00:25:57,198
- We have 1 minute left.
- We have 1 minute left?

699
00:25:57,199 --> 00:25:59,369
(He's quite far from the base camp.)

700
00:25:59,539 --> 00:26:00,769
Jong Min, hurry!

701
00:26:01,139 --> 00:26:03,808
(Will he be able to arrive within 1 minute?)

702
00:26:03,809 --> 00:26:05,179
Se Yoon, you're almost here.

703
00:26:06,279 --> 00:26:08,648
Se Yoon, keep going straight. You're so close.

704
00:26:08,649 --> 00:26:09,819
(Se Yoon)

705
00:26:10,349 --> 00:26:12,579
- Where is it?
- You're almost there.

706
00:26:12,649 --> 00:26:14,389
- Okay.
- You're good. You're here.

707
00:26:14,749 --> 00:26:16,358
- He's guiding Se Yoon in.
- Jong Min, you're so close!

708
00:26:16,359 --> 00:26:17,758
(Only Jong Min remains now.)

709
00:26:17,759 --> 00:26:19,219
Jong Min, you got 30 seconds.

710
00:26:20,129 --> 00:26:21,129
Hurry.

711
00:26:22,259 --> 00:26:23,758
Please Jong Min! Come here!

712
00:26:23,759 --> 00:26:27,999
(If he can't arrive in time, they'll harvest garlic scapes.)

713
00:26:28,269 --> 00:26:30,038
Hey. Darn it. I'm out of breath.

714
00:26:30,039 --> 00:26:32,099
(But his body is reaching its limit.)

715
00:26:32,739 --> 00:26:33,808
You're so close!

716
00:26:33,809 --> 00:26:34,908
(Jong Min, keep running a little more.)

717
00:26:34,909 --> 00:26:36,439
You're the last one!

718
00:26:37,039 --> 00:26:38,079
You're so close.

719
00:26:38,739 --> 00:26:40,778
You can do this. You're so close. I mean it.

720
00:26:40,779 --> 00:26:44,419
(Joon, who came out to meet him, pushes exhausted Jong Min along.)

721
00:26:44,879 --> 00:26:46,088
- Okay.
- Okay.

722
00:26:46,089 --> 00:26:48,049
- Okay.
- I'm so exhausted.

723
00:26:48,989 --> 00:26:51,588
- Jong Min ran very hard.
- I know. He didn't take any breaks.

724
00:26:51,589 --> 00:26:52,589
(I'm exhausted.)

725
00:26:53,259 --> 00:26:55,188
Jong Min, I'm touched.

726
00:26:55,189 --> 00:26:56,198
It was very moving.

727
00:26:56,199 --> 00:26:57,458
He didn't stop at all.

728
00:26:57,459 --> 00:27:00,069
The problem is that we don't know the result yet.

729
00:27:00,429 --> 00:27:02,569
We don't know the result yet.

730
00:27:02,669 --> 00:27:04,298
Could you announce the result?

731
00:27:04,299 --> 00:27:07,408
The result will depend on Jong Min's time...

732
00:27:07,409 --> 00:27:10,239
of arrival because he came last.

733
00:27:10,379 --> 00:27:13,409
The time it took for all the members to arrive at the base camp is...

734
00:27:14,309 --> 00:27:18,178
(Please, we can't work anymore.)

735
00:27:18,179 --> 00:27:19,649
It's 6 minutes and 48 minutes.

736
00:27:20,049 --> 00:27:21,519
- My gosh.
- The mission is accomplished.

737
00:27:21,719 --> 00:27:23,059
- Gosh.
- Twelve seconds.

738
00:27:24,289 --> 00:27:26,128
(He avoided working 3 times in a row.)

739
00:27:26,129 --> 00:27:27,388
Jong Min, we made it thanks to you.

740
00:27:27,389 --> 00:27:28,828
- You ran without giving up.
- In the middle of it...

741
00:27:28,829 --> 00:27:30,098
- That was moving.
- You made it, Jong Min.

742
00:27:30,099 --> 00:27:31,728
My lungs stung because of my allergies.

743
00:27:31,729 --> 00:27:32,928
It's so heartwarming today. It's been a while.

744
00:27:32,929 --> 00:27:34,098
Well done, everyone.

745
00:27:34,099 --> 00:27:36,438
We'll clear all your debts.

746
00:27:36,439 --> 00:27:37,439
Thank you.

747
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:40,939
Starting now, enjoy some free time at the base camp.

748
00:27:41,769 --> 00:27:43,639
- Well done.
- Good job, everyone.

749
00:27:43,739 --> 00:27:45,309
- Can we take a break now?
- Yes.

750
00:27:45,439 --> 00:27:46,548
Gosh, I'm tired.

751
00:27:46,549 --> 00:27:47,578
- Let me sit down.
- I'm so tired.

752
00:27:47,579 --> 00:27:48,749
- Let's lie down.
- I'm really tired.

753
00:27:49,179 --> 00:27:50,548
We were like a running crew.

754
00:27:50,549 --> 00:27:52,378
(Everyone lies down.)

755
00:27:52,379 --> 00:27:54,989
- Didn't I get here really fast?
- Yes.

756
00:27:55,719 --> 00:27:58,118
You did a good job after working nonstop.

757
00:27:58,119 --> 00:27:59,359
(An awakening effect of working 2 consecutive times)

758
00:27:59,729 --> 00:28:01,328
- Well done.
- What I did was excessive.

759
00:28:01,329 --> 00:28:02,388
Well done.

760
00:28:02,389 --> 00:28:03,659
(And his coworker is collapsed from exhaustion.)

761
00:28:04,499 --> 00:28:06,969
(Joon finally lies down while letting out a groan.)

762
00:28:07,799 --> 00:28:09,739
(Spacing out for a moment)

763
00:28:11,569 --> 00:28:12,598
This is great.

764
00:28:12,599 --> 00:28:13,969
(Shaking off the fatigue built up from work and sightseeing)

765
00:28:16,279 --> 00:28:18,278
Actually, I didn't think that we'd succeed.

766
00:28:18,279 --> 00:28:19,308
Me neither.

767
00:28:19,309 --> 00:28:20,649
(A sweet holiday starts.)

768
