01:07:13,229 --> 01:07:15,158
- It's done.
- Should I do it?

2005
01:07:15,159 --> 01:07:16,498
(The 1st runner is back on the path of hardship.)

2006
01:07:16,499 --> 01:07:18,169
Go quickly!

2007
01:07:18,529 --> 01:07:20,839
Hurry up! Come on!

2008
01:07:20,899 --> 01:07:22,909
(He returns quickly.)

2009
01:07:23,369 --> 01:07:24,908
(DinDin, the 2nd runner, joins him.)

2010
01:07:24,909 --> 01:07:26,038
- Okay, go.
- Go. It's the second one.

2011
01:07:26,039 --> 01:07:27,039
Go.

2012
01:07:27,040 --> 01:07:28,379
Show them!

2013
01:07:28,609 --> 01:07:29,678
Let's go!

2014
01:07:29,679 --> 01:07:31,279
(They're fully focused on sleeping indoors.)

2015
01:07:32,209 --> 01:07:34,018
The 3rd runner! Who's the 3rd runner?

2016
01:07:34,019 --> 01:07:36,219
- Turn!
- It's Joon!

2017
01:07:36,289 --> 01:07:37,719
Turn around.

2018
01:07:37,949 --> 01:07:38,988
Good!

2019
01:07:38,989 --> 01:07:40,488
Hurry up! Joon!

2020
01:07:40,489 --> 01:07:41,588
- Go, go!
- His muscles.

2021
01:07:41,589 --> 01:07:43,659
- Go!
- That useless muscle.

2022
01:07:44,229 --> 01:07:46,059
Why did you make your muscles get so big?

2023
01:07:46,259 --> 01:07:47,298
- It didn't fit.
- Lift it.

2024
01:07:47,299 --> 01:07:48,898
- It didn't fit because of his arms.
- Run!

2025
01:07:48,899 --> 01:07:49,899
(They make a perfect turn.)

2026
01:07:50,329 --> 01:07:51,999
- Just a bit more!
- Turn!

2027
01:07:52,099 --> 01:07:53,169
Turn.

2028
01:07:53,299 --> 01:07:54,439
- Okay!
- Go!

2029
01:07:54,499 --> 01:07:55,768
Not yet.

2030
01:07:55,769 --> 01:07:57,268
- Go!
- No!

2031
01:07:57,269 --> 01:07:58,308
I couldn't wear it.

2032
01:07:58,309 --> 01:07:59,709
- Go!
- Go!

2033
01:07:59,909 --> 01:08:02,649
- Run!
- Get going!

2034
01:08:03,079 --> 01:08:04,979
Run!

2035
01:08:05,109 --> 01:08:06,478
(They're currently faster than the first attempt.)

2036
01:08:06,479 --> 01:08:07,618
Run!

2037
01:08:07,619 --> 01:08:08,949
(They're currently faster than the first attempt.)

2038
01:08:09,079 --> 01:08:11,849
(At this rate, the chances of success will go up.)

2039
01:08:12,119 --> 01:08:15,189
(A tearful battle to sleep indoors)

2040
01:08:15,519 --> 01:08:16,528
(It's killing them.)

2041
01:08:16,529 --> 01:08:18,959
- Turn!
- Turn!

2042
01:08:19,329 --> 01:08:21,929
- Hurry, Se Yoon!
- Go! Get going!

2043
01:08:22,029 --> 01:08:23,828
- Go!
- We're almost there.

2044
01:08:23,829 --> 01:08:25,068
We're going fast.

2045
01:08:25,069 --> 01:08:26,398
- Lift it!
- Lift it!

2046
01:08:26,399 --> 01:08:28,399
- Lift it!
- Turn!

2047
01:08:28,439 --> 01:08:29,838
- My heel.
- Lift it!

2048
01:08:29,839 --> 01:08:31,909
I hit my heel.

2049
01:08:32,139 --> 01:08:33,739
Just go! Be quiet.

2050
01:08:34,079 --> 01:08:35,739
- I hit my left heel.
- Be careful.

2051
01:08:35,879 --> 01:08:37,049
Turn!

2052
01:08:37,609 --> 01:08:39,949
Let's go! Make a turn.

2053
01:08:39,979 --> 01:08:42,849
(They run to the final stage.)

2054
01:08:43,749 --> 01:08:45,418
Run, guys!

2055
01:08:45,419 --> 01:08:47,789
We have to get ready to sleep.

2056
01:08:48,019 --> 01:08:49,389
- Hey...
- Jong Min!

2057
01:08:49,659 --> 01:08:50,889
- Give it here.
- Jong Min!

2058
01:08:50,989 --> 01:08:52,358
- Hey.
- DinDin!

2059
01:08:52,359 --> 01:08:53,458
- DinDin.
- I have Joon's!

2060
01:08:53,459 --> 01:08:54,929
- Someone unzipped this.
- DinDin.

2061
01:08:55,529 --> 01:08:57,699
(Will they be able to succeed this time?)

2062
01:08:58,169 --> 01:08:59,538
(They're in a rush.)

2063
01:08:59,539 --> 01:09:01,469
Get ready to sleep. Quickly get ready to sleep.

2064
01:09:01,739 --> 01:09:02,769
I'm ready.

2065
01:09:03,309 --> 01:09:04,609
Are you the only one done?

2066
01:09:04,809 --> 01:09:07,438
(The other members also rush to get ready to sleep.)

2067
01:09:07,439 --> 01:09:08,479
I'm ready.

2068
01:09:10,579 --> 01:09:12,549
I'm done! Hurry up!

2069
01:09:13,379 --> 01:09:14,918
(Jong Min is ready.)

2070
01:09:14,919 --> 01:09:16,619
- Hurry.
- One, two, three.

2071
01:09:16,649 --> 01:09:17,988
- We're ready to sleep!
- We're ready to sleep!

2072
01:09:17,989 --> 01:09:19,119
(They're all ready to sleep.)

2073
01:09:19,489 --> 01:09:22,459
(Did they manage to succeed within 3 minutes 30 seconds?)

2074
01:09:22,559 --> 01:09:24,629
(Please...)

2075
01:09:25,129 --> 01:09:26,899
Mission cleared!

2076
01:09:27,029 --> 01:09:28,029
Did we do it?

2077
01:09:28,959 --> 01:09:30,798
- Did we make it?
- It was a buzzer-beater.

2078
01:09:30,799 --> 01:09:32,369
How much time was left?

2079
01:09:32,469 --> 01:09:33,798
It was a buzzer-beater.

2080
01:09:33,799 --> 01:09:34,969
(The most thrilling buzzer-beater)

2081
01:09:35,099 --> 01:09:36,168
(What a relief.)

2082
01:09:36,169 --> 01:09:37,309
Are you all right, Seon Ho?

2083
01:09:37,969 --> 01:09:40,679
(Even after the dramatic success, they all keep groaning.)

2084
01:09:41,279 --> 01:09:45,079
(They're still out of breath.)

2085
01:09:45,349 --> 01:09:46,748
Let's go.

2086
01:09:46,749 --> 01:09:48,349
Are you all alive?

2087
01:09:48,849 --> 01:09:50,248
It was no joke.

2088
01:09:50,249 --> 01:09:51,489
- Seon Ho.
- Right.

2089
01:09:51,589 --> 01:09:53,572
Seon Ho gave it his all.

2090
01:09:53,739 --> 01:09:55,379
My legs can't move.

2091
01:09:55,404 --> 01:09:57,114
- My legs can't move.
- It's like my body is paralyzed.

2092
01:09:57,232 --> 01:09:58,392
We really did our best.

2093
01:09:59,529 --> 01:10:00,899
- Well done.
- We really...

2094
01:10:01,229 --> 01:10:03,398
- went all out today.
- Unbelievable.

2095
01:10:03,399 --> 01:10:04,829
Starting with the fishing this morning...

2096
01:10:05,429 --> 01:10:06,498
You didn't do that.

2097
01:10:06,499 --> 01:10:07,499
(Feeling awkward)

2098
01:10:07,569 --> 01:10:09,669
- You didn't go there.
- Did you have to say that?

2099
01:10:10,069 --> 01:10:11,438
Seriously.

2100
01:10:11,439 --> 01:10:12,978
I'm just saying they had a hard day.

2101
01:10:12,979 --> 01:10:14,338
Goodness, I'm tired.

2102
01:10:14,339 --> 01:10:15,908
As a result of Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors,

2103
01:10:15,909 --> 01:10:18,148
everyone will sleep indoors in the annex building.

2104
01:10:18,149 --> 01:10:19,419
(They'll be sleeping indoors in the annex building.)

2105
01:10:20,019 --> 01:10:21,649
It's a bit disappointing that it's the annex.

2106
01:10:21,919 --> 01:10:22,919
It's really small.

2107
01:10:23,049 --> 01:10:24,088
You worked hard today.

2108
01:10:24,089 --> 01:10:25,248
Great job.

2109
01:10:25,249 --> 01:10:26,319
Let's get ready for bed.

2110
01:10:26,389 --> 01:10:27,389
All right.

2111
01:10:27,589 --> 01:10:29,389
- Great job.
- Great job today.

2112
01:10:30,389 --> 01:10:32,428
(Getting ready to sleep in the annex...)

2113
01:10:32,429 --> 01:10:34,499
(they barely secured with a buzzer-beater)

2114
01:10:35,359 --> 01:10:37,628
(The sleeping area)

2115
01:10:37,629 --> 01:10:38,698
(Jong Min and Se Yoon are taking a shower first.)

2116
01:10:38,699 --> 01:10:40,099
I'm about to fall asleep.

2117
01:10:40,969 --> 01:10:42,169
Why are they taking so long?

2118
01:10:43,409 --> 01:10:46,509
(The younger guys are waiting for their turn.)

2119
01:10:47,979 --> 01:10:50,278
(Five of them will squeeze into this room to sleep!)

2120
01:10:50,279 --> 01:10:51,549
Seon Ho, where do you want to sleep?

2121
01:10:51,579 --> 01:10:53,518
(It's cozy.)

2122
01:10:53,519 --> 01:10:55,248
Are those holes?

2123
01:10:55,249 --> 01:10:56,548
- For air?
- Yes.

2124
01:10:56,549 --> 01:10:58,119
I'm sorry, but can you cover the holes while you sleep?

2125
01:10:58,419 --> 01:10:59,588
With my hand?

2126
01:10:59,589 --> 01:11:02,258
(Of course, I can do that for you.)

2127
01:11:02,259 --> 01:11:03,428
(Seon Ho is strangely confident.)

2128
01:11:03,429 --> 01:11:04,429
I'll do that for you.

2129
01:11:05,141 --> 01:11:08,346
(The biggest contributor to sleeping indoors: Yoo Seon Ho)

2130
01:11:08,393 --> 01:11:09,902
I can just sleep like this.

2131
01:11:09,903 --> 01:11:11,633
Right. Do at least that much.

2132
01:11:13,633 --> 01:11:14,832
I don't need to do that, right?

2133
01:11:14,833 --> 01:11:15,903
You don't need to do it.

2134
01:11:16,543 --> 01:11:20,673
(The 2nd biggest contributor to sleeping indoors: DinDin)

2135
01:11:21,073 --> 01:11:24,142
(They all burst into laughter because of the holes.)

2136
01:11:24,143 --> 01:11:25,612
You're my happy virus.

2137
01:11:25,613 --> 01:11:28,383
(It's the first all-indoor sleep in a while, and the mood is great.)

2138
01:11:29,083 --> 01:11:30,883
(Moving)

2139
01:11:35,453 --> 01:11:38,593
(Joon heads out.)

2140
01:11:42,333 --> 01:11:45,333
(He suddenly goes to the car.)

2141
01:11:53,543 --> 01:11:54,813
(Looking around)

2142
01:11:54,913 --> 01:11:57,913
(What is he doing so secretly?)

2143
01:12:02,883 --> 01:12:04,983
Here. Write what you want to say.

2144
01:12:05,653 --> 01:12:06,753
We have no time.

2145
01:12:07,893 --> 01:12:08,922
Write them quickly.

2146
01:12:08,923 --> 01:12:12,523
(Actually, tonight is the last night with Seon Ho.)

2147
01:12:13,233 --> 01:12:14,263
So...

2148
01:12:14,463 --> 01:12:17,133
we're planning to do a little event for him.

2149
01:12:17,333 --> 01:12:20,973
Since Seon Ho is an actor, he'd notice.

2150
01:12:21,133 --> 01:12:23,243
He was here for almost four years.

2151
01:12:23,673 --> 01:12:25,142
It would feel...

2152
01:12:25,143 --> 01:12:26,203
(The older guys prepared a small event for Seon Ho.)

2153
01:12:26,243 --> 01:12:28,243
really weird.

2154
01:12:28,913 --> 01:12:30,643
(Jong Min joins.)

2155
01:12:31,383 --> 01:12:33,653
(Se Yoon joins.)

2156
01:12:33,953 --> 01:12:35,052
Hurry up.

2157
01:12:35,053 --> 01:12:36,652
I told DinDin we can't both go.

2158
01:12:36,653 --> 01:12:38,253
He tried to come with me.

2159
01:12:38,583 --> 01:12:40,252
Where's Seon Ho now?

2160
01:12:40,253 --> 01:12:42,492
I told DinDin to stay with him.

2161
01:12:42,493 --> 01:12:43,923
- I came out after that.
- Okay.

2162
01:12:44,993 --> 01:12:47,163
(He's keeping Seon Ho in the room.)

2163
01:12:51,763 --> 01:12:53,502
It feels weird.

2164
01:12:53,503 --> 01:12:55,733
(Meanwhile, Seon Ho is starting to feel that it's coming to an end.)

2165
01:12:56,403 --> 01:12:57,903
Why are you so relaxed?

2166
01:12:58,243 --> 01:13:00,243
- Hurry up!
- I'm doing it as fast as I can!

2167
01:13:01,573 --> 01:13:02,672
(They have to get everything ready before Seon Ho notices.)

2168
01:13:02,673 --> 01:13:04,213
It's Seon Ho's last day.

2169
01:13:04,843 --> 01:13:07,053
(Master craftsmanship)

2170
01:13:07,713 --> 01:13:10,282
We're going to fill this small space.

2171
01:13:10,283 --> 01:13:11,383
- Really?
- Yes.

2172
01:13:11,483 --> 01:13:12,483
Scissors.

2173
01:13:12,484 --> 01:13:13,523
(Bursting)

2174
01:13:14,223 --> 01:13:15,822
We're going to get caught.

2175
01:13:15,823 --> 01:13:17,493
- We'll get caught!
- We might get caught.

2176
01:13:17,823 --> 01:13:19,163
(Se Yoon enters.)

2177
01:13:19,263 --> 01:13:20,263
(He received the baton.)

2178
01:13:20,264 --> 01:13:21,293
Help.

2179
01:13:22,093 --> 01:13:23,862
Hurry up, DinDin!

2180
01:13:23,863 --> 01:13:26,103
Things aren't working properly without you around.

2181
01:13:26,803 --> 01:13:28,403
It looks better with this, right?

2182
01:13:28,803 --> 01:13:30,443
It looks much better with that.

2183
01:13:30,703 --> 01:13:36,383
(The older members are carefully preparing a gift for Seon Ho.)

2184
01:13:36,543 --> 01:13:38,542
Just pack it in as tightly as possible.

2185
01:13:38,543 --> 01:13:39,782
Just think of it as a music box.

2186
01:13:39,783 --> 01:13:41,853
You have to be creative in decorating.

2187
01:13:42,013 --> 01:13:43,882
There are actors.

2188
01:13:43,883 --> 01:13:46,353
(The surprise event for Seon Ho is ready.)

2189
01:13:46,823 --> 01:13:47,823
We're done.

2190
01:13:47,824 --> 01:13:49,863
Did you see this? I took all these pictures.

2191
01:13:50,123 --> 01:13:51,362
Look at the pictures I took.

2192
01:13:51,363 --> 01:13:52,722
Let's hide here.

2193
01:13:52,723 --> 01:13:54,033
Okay.

2194
01:13:55,663 --> 01:13:56,663
Where's Joon?

2195
01:13:56,703 --> 01:13:58,633
They're coming. Let's wait here.

2196
01:13:59,033 --> 01:14:00,302
(Seon Ho gets suspicious as the older guys take long to return.)

2197
01:14:00,303 --> 01:14:01,473
I think that's why.

2198
01:14:02,003 --> 01:14:03,803
It doesn't look like something we can join in.

2199
01:14:04,673 --> 01:14:06,172
If it's coming from Jong Min,

2200
01:14:06,173 --> 01:14:07,942
- it must be serious.
- It didn't look serious, but...

2201
01:14:07,943 --> 01:14:09,573
I just think they're taking a while.

2202
01:14:09,883 --> 01:14:11,482
I don't think it's our place to join in.

2203
01:14:11,483 --> 01:14:12,943
(He said Jong Min and Se Yoon were having a serious talk.)

2204
01:14:14,053 --> 01:14:15,053
When do we open this?

2205
01:14:15,283 --> 01:14:16,352
We should open it when he comes.

2206
01:14:16,353 --> 01:14:17,853
We can't open it yet.

2207
01:14:18,683 --> 01:14:20,353
They want us to come out for a bit.

2208
01:14:22,193 --> 01:14:23,863
There are so many stars.

2209
01:14:24,923 --> 01:14:27,462
(What are they talking about that they even want us to come out?)

2210
01:14:27,463 --> 01:14:30,103
(He's curious.)

2211
01:14:30,233 --> 01:14:31,303
I'll give you a signal.

2212
01:14:32,863 --> 01:14:33,873
Do I open it?

2213
01:14:34,033 --> 01:14:36,333
(He said he'd give you a signal.)

2214
01:14:37,215 --> 01:14:37,984
One...

2215
01:14:38,543 --> 01:14:39,237
Two.

2216
01:14:40,443 --> 01:14:41,361
Three.

2217
01:14:42,373 --> 01:14:43,613
(Peeking)

2218
01:14:43,883 --> 01:14:45,743
(Cue!)

2219
01:14:47,453 --> 01:14:48,513
What is this?

2220
01:14:51,223 --> 01:14:52,652
- So...
- We prepared this for you.

2221
01:14:52,653 --> 01:14:54,022
So this was what took so long.

2222
01:14:54,023 --> 01:14:55,992
We kept getting your attention...

2223
01:14:55,993 --> 01:14:57,692
to prepare for this.

2224
01:14:57,693 --> 01:14:59,322
We heard that this was what actors do.

2225
01:14:59,323 --> 01:15:00,592
We heard that this was what...

2226
01:15:00,593 --> 01:15:02,293
- actors do at the end of a show.
- Right.

2227
01:15:02,963 --> 01:15:04,662
- We kept moving back and forth...
- Right.

2228
01:15:04,663 --> 01:15:05,833
to hang these up.

2229
01:15:05,933 --> 01:15:06,973
- Check out the photos.
- This is awesome.

2230
01:15:07,273 --> 01:15:08,503
When was this?

2231
01:15:09,203 --> 01:15:11,242
- We did all this today...
- Hurry.

2232
01:15:11,243 --> 01:15:12,502
behind your back.

2233
01:15:12,503 --> 01:15:14,073
- Get a shot of this.
- We wrote letters for you.

2234
01:15:14,413 --> 01:15:16,213
- Right here.
- When did you do this?

2235
01:15:16,713 --> 01:15:17,842
It's a must.

2236
01:15:17,843 --> 01:15:19,312
Gosh, I didn't know.

2237
01:15:19,313 --> 01:15:20,712
(It started this morning.)

2238
01:15:20,713 --> 01:15:21,753
- Check out the photos.
- This is awesome.

2239
01:15:21,983 --> 01:15:23,112
When was this?

2240
01:15:23,113 --> 01:15:24,123
(A surprise event for Seon Ho)

2241
01:15:24,483 --> 01:15:26,182
(Before the opening, 6am)

2242
01:15:26,183 --> 01:15:28,253
Okay. Look natural.

2243
01:15:28,923 --> 01:15:29,992
Don't get caught.

2244
01:15:29,993 --> 01:15:31,163
(Before the opening, 6am)

2245
01:15:33,333 --> 01:15:34,533
Close the door.

2246
01:15:35,863 --> 01:15:39,533
(The four older brothers gathered without Seon Ho knowing.)

2247
01:15:41,573 --> 01:15:45,842
(To Seon Ho, who will be having his last shoot,)

2248
01:15:45,843 --> 01:15:48,442
(the other members wrote letters from their hearts.)

2249
01:15:48,443 --> 01:15:51,212
We did all this today behind your back.

2250
01:15:51,213 --> 01:15:52,543
- Get a shot of this.
- We wrote letters for you.

2251
01:15:52,683 --> 01:15:57,382
(Just like that,)

2252
01:15:57,383 --> 01:16:02,553
(the older brothers confessed their hearts throughout the day.)

2253
01:16:02,993 --> 01:16:04,093
(Checking)

2254
01:16:07,893 --> 01:16:10,663
(Approaching)

2255
01:16:10,703 --> 01:16:14,103
(Our youngest forever, I love you more than kimchi stew!)

2256
01:16:15,903 --> 01:16:17,203
How do we get rid of the water?

2257
01:16:17,703 --> 01:16:19,503
- What?
- How do we get rid of the water?

2258
01:16:20,213 --> 01:16:21,973
Gosh, look to your right.

2259
01:16:23,543 --> 01:16:25,143
Look at the sky. I should take pictures.

2260
01:16:28,453 --> 01:16:30,023
(Holding up)

2261
01:16:30,253 --> 01:16:31,452
(The time we spent together felt a lot more precious than I thought.)

2262
01:16:31,453 --> 01:16:32,752
(You're the best youngest member.)

2263
01:16:32,753 --> 01:16:34,053
(I love you.)

2264
01:16:39,223 --> 01:16:42,763
(A V without Seon Ho knowing)

2265
01:16:43,263 --> 01:16:46,832
(A smile of an older brother)

2266
01:16:46,833 --> 01:16:48,102
(My bright and positive younger brother, Seon Ho!)

2267
01:16:48,103 --> 01:16:49,272
(I felt so happy thanks to you...)

2268
01:16:49,273 --> 01:16:50,373
(during the trips we had together.)

2269
01:16:57,083 --> 01:16:58,682
(Dear Seon Ho...)

2270
01:16:58,683 --> 01:17:03,622
(Toward the youngest on his final trip,)

2271
01:17:03,623 --> 01:17:09,353
(they all sent messages of love.)

2272
01:17:09,423 --> 01:17:11,463
(The time we spent together felt a lot more precious than I thought.)

2273
01:17:12,163 --> 01:17:15,933
(Our youngest forever, I love you more than kimchi stew!)

2274
01:17:23,643 --> 01:17:30,813
(He checks each farewell message with his eyes.)

2275
01:17:32,343 --> 01:17:33,953
We still managed to do it without getting caught.

2276
01:17:35,653 --> 01:17:37,022
- Gosh.
- You wrote a lot.

2277
01:17:37,023 --> 01:17:39,053
- What must I do with all this?
- Read it for him.

2278
01:17:39,453 --> 01:17:41,623
- Gosh.
- Read it with a sincere heart.

2279
01:17:41,993 --> 01:17:43,253
Let's read them for him.

2280
01:17:44,363 --> 01:17:46,162
The eldest should start.

2281
01:17:46,163 --> 01:17:47,193
Right.

2282
01:17:49,263 --> 01:17:50,333
Seon Ho!

2283
01:17:50,533 --> 01:17:51,733
You didn't write that.

2284
01:17:51,903 --> 01:17:54,203
- Gosh.
- You didn't write that.

2285
01:17:54,403 --> 01:17:55,672
I didn't write that.

2286
01:17:55,673 --> 01:17:57,573
Jong Min doesn't disappoint even on my last day.

2287
01:17:57,873 --> 01:18:00,513
Seon Ho! The time we spent together...

2288
01:18:00,773 --> 01:18:02,313
felt a lot more precious than I thought.

2289
01:18:03,043 --> 01:18:05,743
I will always cherish your kindness and innocence.

2290
01:18:06,113 --> 01:18:08,453
You're the best youngest member, Seon Ho. I love you.

2291
01:18:11,053 --> 01:18:12,123
I love you.

2292
01:18:12,253 --> 01:18:13,253
This is...

2293
01:18:13,254 --> 01:18:15,123
- This really speaks to me.
- As for me...

2294
01:18:15,223 --> 01:18:16,722
- It's from his heart.
- As for me,

2295
01:18:16,723 --> 01:18:18,822
this is the best compliment I can make.

2296
01:18:18,823 --> 01:18:20,233
I've never said this to anyone else.

2297
01:18:21,093 --> 01:18:22,293
Our youngest forever,

2298
01:18:23,033 --> 01:18:26,332
I love you more than kimchi stew!

2299
01:18:26,333 --> 01:18:29,672
(I love you more than kimchi stew!)

2300
01:18:29,673 --> 01:18:32,202
Seon Ho. There aren't many who I love more than kimchi stew.

2301
01:18:32,203 --> 01:18:33,372
There are just a few. I'm serious.

2302
01:18:33,373 --> 01:18:35,773
You know how much he loves kimchi stew.

2303
01:18:37,543 --> 01:18:38,543
Mine is short.

2304
01:18:38,813 --> 01:18:41,182
I'm a thinker. You know this, don't you?

2305
01:18:41,183 --> 01:18:42,413
- Ours are short.
- Right.

2306
01:18:42,913 --> 01:18:45,623
My bright and positive younger brother, Seon Ho!

2307
01:18:46,383 --> 01:18:49,622
I felt so happy thanks to you during the trips we had together.

2308
01:18:49,623 --> 01:18:51,593
Gosh, my tears have dried up.

2309
01:18:52,123 --> 01:18:53,293
Gosh.

2310
01:18:53,593 --> 01:18:55,332
- Joon and I talked a lot.
- It was nice and simple.

2311
01:18:55,333 --> 01:18:56,932
- Right.
- Right.

2312
01:18:56,933 --> 01:18:58,532
- Today's highlight, DinDin.
- Right.

2313
01:18:58,533 --> 01:19:00,003
- Go, Lim Cheol.
- It's DinDin.

2314
01:19:00,503 --> 01:19:01,873
DinDin...

2315
01:19:02,373 --> 01:19:04,202
had a lot of affection toward Seon Ho.

2316
01:19:04,203 --> 01:19:05,772
- Right.
- Ever since the start.

2317
01:19:05,773 --> 01:19:06,843
Right.

2318
01:19:09,813 --> 01:19:10,842
Seon Ho!

2319
01:19:10,843 --> 01:19:12,513
(To the youngest who he has spent 3 years and a half with)

2320
01:19:17,823 --> 01:19:20,122
You were like a present that came to us.

2321
01:19:20,123 --> 01:19:24,663
(Seon Ho! You were like a present that came to us.)

2322
01:19:29,333 --> 01:19:30,503
The more I see you,

2323
01:19:31,503 --> 01:19:33,703
you feel like a piece of treasure that is hard to find these days.

2324
01:19:37,973 --> 01:19:43,982
(He sheds tears in the end.)

2325
01:19:43,983 --> 01:19:47,413
(He sheds tears in the end.)

2326
01:19:48,013 --> 01:19:49,413
- Gosh!
- Hang in there.

2327
01:19:52,053 --> 01:19:54,152
Gosh, this is making me choke up as well.

2328
01:19:54,153 --> 01:19:55,493
I didn't expect to be like this.

2329
01:19:56,023 --> 01:19:57,563
Try to finish it up.

2330
01:19:57,763 --> 01:19:59,723
Keep going. It's great to hear.

2331
01:20:00,233 --> 01:20:01,963
That was why you should've written a short letter like me.

2332
01:20:01,993 --> 01:20:03,262
(He barely manages to get himself together and carries on.)

2333
01:20:03,263 --> 01:20:04,333
Carry on.

2334
01:20:05,733 --> 01:20:09,703
All right. You were like a present that came to us.

2335
01:20:10,273 --> 01:20:11,342
The more I see you,

2336
01:20:11,343 --> 01:20:12,643
you feel like a piece of treasure that is hard to find these days.

2337
01:20:13,203 --> 01:20:15,313
We will continue to be family members.

2338
01:20:16,173 --> 01:20:17,212
You've been through so much.

2339
01:20:17,213 --> 01:20:18,843
I love you more than anyone, my younger brother.

2340
01:20:19,443 --> 01:20:20,482
Thinking about it now,

2341
01:20:20,483 --> 01:20:21,513
there are many things I feel bad about.

2342
01:20:21,883 --> 01:20:23,313
I will pay you back throughout life.

2343
01:20:23,623 --> 01:20:25,653
I hope you will continue to shine just like how you are shining now.

2344
01:20:26,083 --> 01:20:27,153
I love you.

2345
01:20:28,853 --> 01:20:30,362
(He tried to keep his tears,)

2346
01:20:30,363 --> 01:20:33,223
(but he breaks down at the thought of the last trip with him.)

2347
01:20:33,493 --> 01:20:35,133
DinDin will have many things he feels bad about.

2348
01:20:36,633 --> 01:20:38,563
That is why he's shedding a lot of tears.

2349
01:20:39,133 --> 01:20:41,903
There are 2,200 people in line that he has to repay in life.

2350
01:20:43,133 --> 01:20:44,143
Thank you.

2351
01:20:44,703 --> 01:20:47,112
- Gosh, this feels quite awkward.
- Gosh.

2352
01:20:47,113 --> 01:20:48,912
It's not like we're not going to see each other.

2353
01:20:48,913 --> 01:20:51,283
- Right.
- Don't cry.

2354
01:20:51,583 --> 01:20:52,682
Well...

2355
01:20:52,683 --> 01:20:54,453
- Are you crying, Jong Min?
- Yes.

2356
01:20:55,413 --> 01:20:56,413
(Wiping)

2357
01:20:56,414 --> 01:20:57,483
Really?

2358
01:20:58,283 --> 01:20:59,523
I have a bad allergy.

2359
01:21:01,253 --> 01:21:03,053
- You should stay at home in spring.
- Gosh.

2360
01:21:03,193 --> 01:21:04,962
Why is everyone being like this?

2361
01:21:04,963 --> 01:21:06,892
You should find another job in spring.

2362
01:21:06,893 --> 01:21:08,932
- Get a temporary part-time job.
- This is black comedy.

2363
01:21:08,933 --> 01:21:10,563
This is black comedy.

2364
01:21:10,663 --> 01:21:11,903
- Gosh.
- Right.

2365
01:21:12,533 --> 01:21:13,773
Seon Ho.

2366
01:21:14,403 --> 01:21:15,633
Don't you have anything to say to your older brothers?

2367
01:21:16,673 --> 01:21:18,973
Why wouldn't I? I have so much to say.

2368
01:21:19,873 --> 01:21:21,713
I just had so much fun.

2369
01:21:21,873 --> 01:21:23,213
I felt happy as well.

2370
01:21:24,583 --> 01:21:26,513
When else would I be able to have this experience?

2371
01:21:26,813 --> 01:21:29,483
We traveled around the country together.

2372
01:21:32,753 --> 01:21:35,623
Of course, this will be the last trip...

2373
01:21:36,493 --> 01:21:38,363
in 2 Days 1 Night.

2374
01:21:38,993 --> 01:21:41,563
But you guys will be my reliable older brothers forever.

2375
01:21:42,993 --> 01:21:44,532
- I love that.
- Right.

2376
01:21:44,533 --> 01:21:46,062
(Seon Ho made a reliable family after a long journey.)

2377
01:21:46,063 --> 01:21:48,603
I feel grateful as well.

2378
01:21:48,933 --> 01:21:50,943
In times of good or bad or any struggles,

2379
01:21:51,843 --> 01:21:54,142
I hope that you will call us first.

2380
01:21:54,143 --> 01:21:55,212
- Of course.
- right.

2381
01:21:55,213 --> 01:21:57,483
- We worked so hard on this.
- Right.

2382
01:21:57,743 --> 01:21:59,842
- What do we do with this?
- Can we have the cake?

2383
01:21:59,843 --> 01:22:01,013
Hold on. Stand there again.

2384
01:22:01,583 --> 01:22:03,953
- I'll read the letter again.
- No?

2385
01:22:04,823 --> 01:22:06,252
- Seon Ho!
- Shut it. We'll use the one before.

2386
01:22:06,253 --> 01:22:07,253
You were like a present that came to us.

2387
01:22:07,254 --> 01:22:08,323
Forget it.

2388
01:22:08,393 --> 01:22:10,763
(He tries to cover up his embarrassing moment.)

2389
01:22:11,393 --> 01:22:14,093
(He starts teasing him.)

2390
01:22:14,693 --> 01:22:15,762
"We will continue to be..."

2391
01:22:15,763 --> 01:22:17,332
(Like always,)

2392
01:22:17,333 --> 01:22:20,063
(they laugh in joy while leaving behind the sadness.)

2393
01:22:20,473 --> 01:22:23,102
- Let's head in.
- Right.

2394
01:22:23,103 --> 01:22:25,073
- Take a picture.
- Right.

2395
01:22:25,573 --> 01:22:28,043
Gosh, it's making me choke up.

2396
01:22:29,313 --> 01:22:31,343
- I don't want to cry.
- Take a picture for us.

2397
01:22:32,313 --> 01:22:33,412
I'll take it.

2398
01:22:33,413 --> 01:22:35,712
Look over here. One, two, three!

2399
01:22:35,713 --> 01:22:39,082
(A graduation party for Seon Ho prepared by the older brothers)

2400
01:22:39,083 --> 01:22:40,552
I can take all of these, right?

2401
01:22:40,553 --> 01:22:41,753
- Of course.
- Right.

2402
01:22:41,993 --> 01:22:43,623
I must take everything home.

2403
01:22:43,923 --> 01:22:46,423
Gosh, I was fine before, but it made me choke up.

2404
01:22:49,393 --> 01:22:51,063
Gosh, the end has come like this.

2405
01:22:51,633 --> 01:22:52,633
Right.

2406
01:22:52,803 --> 01:22:55,173
Did you join when you were 20?

2407
01:22:55,303 --> 01:22:57,042
- I joined when I was 21.
- Right.

2408
01:22:57,043 --> 01:22:58,043
- Right.
- Really?

2409
01:22:58,173 --> 01:22:59,302
- Gosh!
- How old are you now?

2410
01:22:59,303 --> 01:23:00,342
I'm 25 now.

2411
01:23:00,343 --> 01:23:02,143
- You joined when you were 21?
- Yes.

2412
01:23:02,373 --> 01:23:04,513
I spent all of my 20s here.

2413
01:23:04,783 --> 01:23:06,412
It's like you graduated from college.

2414
01:23:06,413 --> 01:23:07,583
- Right.
- Right.

2415
01:23:10,013 --> 01:23:13,483
(He joined 2 Days 1 Night in December 2022.)

2416
01:23:13,853 --> 01:23:15,923
(It's great to see you!)

2417
01:23:16,493 --> 01:23:20,533
(The awkward beginning of the semester went by.)

2418
01:23:20,593 --> 01:23:21,733
- Let's go!
- Yes!

2419
01:23:21,963 --> 01:23:23,032
Who are we?

2420
01:23:23,033 --> 01:23:24,333
- We're 2 Days 1 Night!
- We're 2 Days 1 Night!

2421
01:23:25,663 --> 01:23:30,643
(They ran together for 3 years and 6 months.)

2422
01:23:31,273 --> 01:23:35,943
(The youngest member has now graduated.)

2423
01:23:37,083 --> 01:23:38,742
It doesn't feel like we're parting.

2424
01:23:38,743 --> 01:23:39,842
- Right.
- Right.

2425
01:23:39,843 --> 01:23:41,613
- It doesn't feel like that at all.
- Right.

2426
01:23:41,683 --> 01:23:43,613
On top of that,

2427
01:23:43,953 --> 01:23:46,752
we didn't focus on sending you away today.

2428
01:23:46,753 --> 01:23:49,223
- We did a regular shoot on purpose.
- Right.

2429
01:23:49,423 --> 01:23:50,822
- This might've been better.
- Right.

2430
01:23:50,823 --> 01:23:52,792
It would've been tough if we focused on that.

2431
01:23:52,793 --> 01:23:54,062
(They enjoyed the trip comfortably as it felt like usual.)

2432
01:23:54,063 --> 01:23:55,063
Right.

2433
01:23:55,963 --> 01:23:59,362
It would've been tough if it was a farewell trip.

2434
01:23:59,363 --> 01:24:00,833
- Right.
- Right.

2435
01:24:01,003 --> 01:24:03,102
I want to finish things with a smile as well.

2436
01:24:03,103 --> 01:24:04,473
- Right.
- Right.

2437
01:24:05,243 --> 01:24:06,802
I think Jong Hyun is crying.

2438
01:24:06,803 --> 01:24:08,043
Gosh, no.

2439
01:24:08,643 --> 01:24:09,843
I'm a feeler.

2440
01:24:11,213 --> 01:24:13,913
It turns out that it had been three and half years.

2441
01:24:14,783 --> 01:24:17,183
We spent a long time together.

2442
01:24:17,653 --> 01:24:18,982
I didn't really realize it...

2443
01:24:18,983 --> 01:24:21,793
when we saw each other once every two weeks.

2444
01:24:23,023 --> 01:24:27,693
We had great times together thanks to you, Seon Ho.

2445
01:24:28,293 --> 01:24:33,163
We will look forward to your future endeavors.

2446
01:24:33,603 --> 01:24:34,633
Great.

2447
01:24:34,733 --> 01:24:37,473
You've spent three and a half years with us.

2448
01:24:37,873 --> 01:24:39,343
Please tell us how you're feeling.

2449
01:24:40,673 --> 01:24:42,443
If I start talking about it, I can go on forever.

2450
01:24:46,243 --> 01:24:49,752
First of all, of course, I want to thank the members...

2451
01:24:49,753 --> 01:24:50,823
(Of course, he's grateful to the members who've been with him.)

2452
01:24:51,023 --> 01:24:52,283
the production crew...

2453
01:24:54,193 --> 01:24:58,223
I want to say a huge thank you once again.

2454
01:24:59,363 --> 01:25:02,133
To be honest, I'm not good at remembering people's names.

2455
01:25:02,893 --> 01:25:06,633
But we've been seeing each other every two weeks here, right?

2456
01:25:08,133 --> 01:25:09,273
So now,

2457
01:25:10,703 --> 01:25:15,843
we've gotten so close that looking at their faces makes me laugh.

2458
01:25:16,973 --> 01:25:19,042
I'll never be able to forget them for the rest of my life.

2459
01:25:19,043 --> 01:25:21,382
(Saying goodbye to the crew members he's opened his heart to)

2460
01:25:21,383 --> 01:25:25,453
So you guys are all sleeping together tonight.

2461
01:25:25,553 --> 01:25:27,953
You can catch up on the stories you missed tonight...

2462
01:25:28,693 --> 01:25:30,493
before going to sleep.

2463
01:25:30,593 --> 01:25:32,262
Okay. All right, everyone.

2464
01:25:32,263 --> 01:25:34,062
- Thank you so much.
- You should clap the slate.

2465
01:25:34,063 --> 01:25:35,592
Okay. I'll clap the slate one last time.

2466
01:25:35,593 --> 01:25:38,062
- Do it with all your heart.
- With all your heart and force.

2467
01:25:38,063 --> 01:25:40,003
Make it look beautiful and touching.

2468
01:25:40,433 --> 01:25:42,203
Thank you so much...

2469
01:25:45,373 --> 01:25:46,473
for everything over the years.

2470
01:25:49,213 --> 01:25:50,783
It's more important to make this emotional.

2471
01:25:51,143 --> 01:25:53,212
Focus on your emotions. It's more important.

2472
01:25:53,213 --> 01:25:54,412
I'll just do it.

2473
01:25:54,413 --> 01:25:55,453
- Okay.
- Go ahead.

2474
01:25:55,513 --> 01:25:57,783
All right. Thank you for everything.

2475
01:25:58,453 --> 01:26:00,422
I'll clap the slate. One, two, three.

2476
01:26:00,423 --> 01:26:02,092
(Seon Ho's final slate)

2477
01:26:02,093 --> 01:26:03,152
Thank you.

2478
01:26:03,153 --> 01:26:04,993
- Well done.
- Thanks.

2479
01:26:05,063 --> 01:26:06,563
Yun Ji is crying a lot.

2480
01:26:08,463 --> 01:26:10,603
(A few staff members are breaking down in tears.)

2481
01:26:10,803 --> 01:26:11,862
- I know.
- Really?

2482
01:26:11,863 --> 01:26:13,232
- She's crying.
- Really?

2483
01:26:13,233 --> 01:26:15,072
- I didn't know.
- She's crying?

2484
01:26:15,073 --> 01:26:16,233
(Please don't cry.)

2485
01:26:16,733 --> 01:26:19,343
Don't cry. If you cry, I'll doodle on your face.

2486
01:26:20,003 --> 01:26:22,443
I'll do the same to the production crew, okay?

2487
01:26:24,883 --> 01:26:28,753
(After the night of the penalty for tears)

2488
01:26:29,053 --> 01:26:33,353
(The morning sun is up.)

2489
01:26:34,453 --> 01:26:39,163
(The second day in Namhae with an exceptionally clear sky)

2490
01:26:40,023 --> 01:26:41,393
(Burst open)

2491
01:26:49,833 --> 01:26:51,503
(The one who cried 1)

2492
01:26:52,403 --> 01:26:54,343
(The one who cried 2)

2493
01:26:54,913 --> 01:26:56,873
(Giggling)

2494
01:26:58,683 --> 01:27:01,453
(Clearly, he's the culprit.)

2495
01:27:02,413 --> 01:27:05,953
(It seems he actually doodled on the faces for crying last night.)

2496
01:27:06,953 --> 01:27:09,852
(Seon Ho didn't cry though.)

2497
01:27:09,853 --> 01:27:10,562
Let's go.

2498
01:27:11,363 --> 01:27:12,663
Let's go and eat, Seon Ho.

2499
01:27:13,123 --> 01:27:14,533
- Let's go.
- The last meal.

2500
01:27:15,133 --> 01:27:18,032
Yesterday was amazing, and today is just as incredible.

2501
01:27:18,033 --> 01:27:19,702
There isn't a single cloud in the sky.

2502
01:27:19,703 --> 01:27:20,932
It feels like fall.

2503
01:27:20,933 --> 01:27:21,933
- I know.
- Right.

2504
01:27:21,934 --> 01:27:23,133
- How nice.
- Look over there.

2505
01:27:23,273 --> 01:27:24,903
- No clouds at all.
- What? What are we looking at?

2506
01:27:25,173 --> 01:27:26,173
The sky.

2507
01:27:27,943 --> 01:27:30,513
It's like we're in Switzerland right now.

2508
01:27:31,516 --> 01:27:32,546
The sky.

2509
01:27:33,083 --> 01:27:34,783
You should go stand over there, Seon Ho.

2510
01:27:36,313 --> 01:27:37,622
This is perfect.

2511
01:27:37,623 --> 01:27:39,523
(Taking photos against a stunning backdrop is a must.)

2512
01:27:40,693 --> 01:27:42,253
This spot is perfect for photos.

2513
01:27:42,323 --> 01:27:44,463
This neighborhood is so beautiful.

2514
01:27:45,163 --> 01:27:46,863
- My goodness.
- This is nice.

2515
01:27:48,093 --> 01:27:49,732
The vibes here are just unreal.

2516
01:27:49,733 --> 01:27:51,503
I love this neighborhood.

2517
01:27:53,133 --> 01:27:54,303
What are they doing?

2518
01:27:54,603 --> 01:27:55,672
(Just then, the members spot something.)

2519
01:27:55,673 --> 01:27:56,803
- What's going on?
- I don't know.

2520
01:27:57,103 --> 01:27:58,802
- What are they doing?
- I guess we're eating...

2521
01:27:58,803 --> 01:28:00,743
- with the entire crew.
- Are we eating together?

2522
01:28:01,073 --> 01:28:02,412
Are we all eating together?

2523
01:28:02,413 --> 01:28:04,013
Apparently, we're eating from the food truck.

2524
01:28:04,413 --> 01:28:05,713
- Really?
- Yes.

2525
01:28:06,213 --> 01:28:07,453
This is so nice.

2526
01:28:09,313 --> 01:28:11,223
Are they just giving us food?

2527
01:28:11,283 --> 01:28:13,523
Seon Ho is leaving us one last gift before he goes.

2528
01:28:18,163 --> 01:28:19,293
- She...
- What?

2529
01:28:19,763 --> 01:28:20,763
What's with Yun Ji?

2530
01:28:21,263 --> 01:28:22,693
She must've cried a lot.

2531
01:28:23,193 --> 01:28:24,333
What happened to Director Yun Ji?

2532
01:28:24,663 --> 01:28:25,703
I don't know.

2533
01:28:26,233 --> 01:28:27,702
- The doodle...
- Was she feeling the same way?

2534
01:28:27,703 --> 01:28:28,872
They must've had so much fun drawing that.

2535
01:28:28,873 --> 01:28:30,873
I guess you cried just as much as I did.

2536
01:28:31,203 --> 01:28:32,372
- My gosh.
- We look the same.

2537
01:28:32,373 --> 01:28:33,403
We're a couple.

2538
01:28:34,173 --> 01:28:36,813
The audio engineer has the doodle on his face.

2539
01:28:37,543 --> 01:28:38,913
- Which one?
- Who?

2540
01:28:39,713 --> 01:28:40,713
Right.

2541
01:28:40,983 --> 01:28:42,082
- The audio engineer.
- Yes.

2542
01:28:42,083 --> 01:28:43,583
(Se Yoon's beard is widely popular.)

2543
01:28:44,453 --> 01:28:47,153
(Quite a few staff members have drawings on their faces too.)

2544
01:28:47,993 --> 01:28:50,963
(Crying)

2545
01:28:56,963 --> 01:28:59,403
(If you cry, you get busted.)

2546
01:29:03,873 --> 01:29:05,873
- Byung Jin must've cried a lot.
- He cried.

2547
01:29:06,203 --> 01:29:08,173
- Byung Jin must've cried a lot.
- He cried a lot.

2548
01:29:08,343 --> 01:29:09,673
- Seriously...
- Seon Ho.

2549
01:29:10,073 --> 01:29:11,143
Seon Ho.

2550
01:29:11,213 --> 01:29:13,643
Myung Kwan must've been bullied because he's the youngest.

2551
01:29:15,153 --> 01:29:17,453
(The truth is that he cried because he was sad over Seon Ho.)

2552
01:29:18,423 --> 01:29:19,883
The lighting engineer didn't cry.

2553
01:29:21,523 --> 01:29:23,592
- He...
- He didn't cry.

2554
01:29:23,593 --> 01:29:24,923
He didn't cry at all.

2555
01:29:25,623 --> 01:29:28,563
(Chuckling)

2556
01:29:29,363 --> 01:29:30,963
I feel like crying.

2557
01:29:34,133 --> 01:29:35,332
He's crying.

2558
01:29:35,333 --> 01:29:39,373
(Seon Ho becomes emotional.)

2559
01:29:40,813 --> 01:29:44,613
(To think about leaving the people he's grown so attached to)

2560
01:29:46,013 --> 01:29:47,453
Why do I feel like crying?

2561
01:29:55,453 --> 01:29:57,222
(Barely managing to compose himself, he takes his steps forward.)

2562
01:29:57,223 --> 01:29:58,893
Let's just enjoy our meal.

2563
01:29:59,163 --> 01:30:00,793
Seon Ho, look at that.

2564
01:30:01,080 --> 01:30:03,080
- That's...
- Just look at that.

2565
01:30:03,519 --> 01:30:04,224
Right.

2566
01:30:05,363 --> 01:30:07,902
It must not have been easy to put all of this together.

2567
01:30:07,903 --> 01:30:09,203
I guess you didn't read this last night.

2568
01:30:10,273 --> 01:30:13,472
(Cheering messages sent by the crew,)

2569
01:30:13,473 --> 01:30:16,613
(wishing Seon Ho a rosy path ahead)

2570
01:30:18,683 --> 01:30:24,953
(To Seon Ho graduating from 2 Days 1 Night)

2571
01:30:27,223 --> 01:30:32,623
(From all the production crew who love Seon Ho)

2572
01:30:32,863 --> 01:30:34,232
(What's the capital of India?)

2573
01:30:34,233 --> 01:30:36,393
(Indonesia)

2574
01:30:36,463 --> 01:30:38,633
(We have a real treasure.)

2575
01:30:38,703 --> 01:30:41,333
(A striking first encounter with Seon Ho)

2576
01:30:41,503 --> 01:30:42,573
Look at the snow.

2577
01:30:42,973 --> 01:30:50,143
(The arrival of an unpredictable youngest member)

2578
01:30:51,413 --> 01:30:54,452
(Whether in the sweltering heat...)

2579
01:30:54,453 --> 01:30:56,783
(or the freezing cold,)

2580
01:30:58,083 --> 01:31:05,393
(he worked harder than anyone else.)

2581
01:31:05,593 --> 01:31:07,632
(Seon Ho!)

2582
01:31:07,633 --> 01:31:09,293
(I love you!)

2583
01:31:10,333 --> 01:31:13,762
(So everyone loved him.)

2584
01:31:13,763 --> 01:31:19,843
(The eternal youngest member of 2 Days 1 Night)

2585
01:31:21,273 --> 01:31:24,143
(We were so happy to be with you...)

2586
01:31:24,213 --> 01:31:28,053
(for the past 3 and a half years.)

2587
01:31:28,083 --> 01:31:29,283
Bring a pen. He's crying.

2588
01:31:29,853 --> 01:31:31,553
Seon Ho, are you crying?

2589
01:31:32,223 --> 01:31:33,423
- Yes.
- He's sobbing.

2590
01:31:33,953 --> 01:31:35,422
He finally burst into tears.

2591
01:31:35,423 --> 01:31:37,453
He's been holding it in since yesterday.

2592
01:31:40,263 --> 01:31:41,893
(Patting his back)

2593
01:31:42,593 --> 01:31:46,903
(Seon Ho finally bursts into tears that he has held in.)

2594
01:31:47,003 --> 01:31:48,702
Did you just cry? Get me a pen.

2595
01:31:48,703 --> 01:31:50,803
(Joking)

2596
01:31:51,443 --> 01:31:53,142
- Where's a pen?
- Bring a pen.

2597
01:31:53,143 --> 01:31:54,243
He's crying.

2598
01:31:54,443 --> 01:31:55,443
(Swift pen delivery)

2599
01:31:55,444 --> 01:31:57,643
- Come here.
- My goodness.

2600
01:31:58,143 --> 01:31:59,782
(Come here.)

2601
01:31:59,783 --> 01:32:01,353
- Come here.
- I'll do it.

2602
01:32:03,053 --> 01:32:05,222
Stay still. I'm sorry, Seon Ho.

2603
01:32:05,223 --> 01:32:06,253
(You cried, so you have to take the penalty.)

2604
01:32:07,253 --> 01:32:08,793
- What?
- Hey, Seon Ho.

2605
01:32:09,093 --> 01:32:11,092
- Yes?
- Team Lighting, come here.

2606
01:32:11,093 --> 01:32:12,162
Team Security.

2607
01:32:12,163 --> 01:32:14,123
(It's time to take the final group photo.)

2608
01:32:14,633 --> 01:32:16,363
Let's go. Come here, Seong Ho.

2609
01:32:16,493 --> 01:32:17,633
Dong Hoon, come running.

2610
01:32:19,203 --> 01:32:21,473
Dong Hoon, just record a video and take a screenshot later.

2611
01:32:21,833 --> 01:32:24,103
I think Dong Hoon is just trying to look cool by doing that.

2612
01:32:26,203 --> 01:32:28,713
It's hard for them to stay still because they're old.

2613
01:32:29,673 --> 01:32:30,942
Let's make it quick.

2614
01:32:30,943 --> 01:32:32,013
(Park Tae Hee, the writer in charge of Seon Ho, cried)

2615
01:32:33,043 --> 01:32:34,452
(Kim Yong Han, the cameraman in charge of Seon Ho, cried a lot)

2616
01:32:34,453 --> 01:32:35,913
Seon Ho, say something.

2617
01:32:36,453 --> 01:32:38,683
Thank you for everything.

2618
01:32:38,723 --> 01:32:40,283
Let's meet again.

2619
01:32:41,393 --> 01:32:43,053
Seon Ho, we'll be rooting for you.

2620
01:32:43,363 --> 01:32:46,463
- 2 Days 1 Night!
- 2 Days 1 Night!

2621
01:32:50,233 --> 01:32:52,662
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

2622
01:32:52,663 --> 01:32:54,162
(You've done a great job, Seon Ho.)

2623
01:32:54,163 --> 01:32:56,272
- Thank you, Seon Ho.
- Thank you.

2624
01:32:56,273 --> 01:32:57,973
- Good work, Seon Ho.
- Thank you.

2625
01:32:58,173 --> 01:32:59,702
- Good work.
- Thank you.

2626
01:32:59,703 --> 01:33:03,913
(The graduation ceremony of our beloved member, Seon Ho, is over.)

2627
01:33:04,043 --> 01:33:05,983
(Next episode)

2628
01:33:06,583 --> 01:33:07,583
I'm very nervous.

2629
01:33:07,584 --> 01:33:10,353
The moment I stepped into KBS, I started to feel worried.

2630
01:33:10,553 --> 01:33:14,353
I'm feeling a bit of thrill, and I'm looking forward to it.

2631
01:33:18,972 --> 01:33:21,293
(The ultimate all-rounder and variety veteran, Lee Yong Jin)

2632
01:33:21,993 --> 01:33:24,163
(The unpredictable variety rookie, Lee Ki Taek)

2633
01:33:25,233 --> 01:33:28,003
(The new members are joining.)

2634
01:33:31,803 --> 01:33:34,412
- Yong Jin, in your dress shoes?
- Let's just go.

2635
01:33:34,413 --> 01:33:37,612
(The variety veteran's unmatched adaptability)

2636
01:33:37,613 --> 01:33:39,743
Yong Jin is insane. What do we do with him?

2637
01:33:40,383 --> 01:33:41,613
(Overflowing stamina)

2638
01:33:42,253 --> 01:33:43,953
(Sexy brain)

2639
01:33:44,083 --> 01:33:46,023
(Mumbling)

2640
01:33:46,153 --> 01:33:47,153
(Perfectly adapted to 2 Days 1 Night, Yong Jin)

2641
01:33:48,153 --> 01:33:49,853
(Overflowing puppy-like charms)

2642
01:33:50,423 --> 01:33:52,093
(A bit clumsy for his physique)

2643
01:33:52,393 --> 01:33:53,422
(What's with him?)

2644
01:33:53,423 --> 01:33:54,662
(Clumsy Taek)

2645
01:33:54,663 --> 01:33:55,762
Can you do this?

2646
01:33:55,763 --> 01:33:56,793
(Squeaky)

2647
01:33:56,893 --> 01:33:58,933
(Uncoordinated Taek)

2648
01:33:59,563 --> 01:34:00,902
(The youngest member with unpredictable charms, Taek)

2649
01:34:00,903 --> 01:34:02,373
- Two, three. Jump!
- Jump!

2650
01:34:02,703 --> 01:34:04,803
(The upcoming new journeys...)

2651
01:34:05,443 --> 01:34:08,243
(with Yong Jin and Ki Taek)

2652
01:34:08,943 --> 01:34:12,412
(Curious about the chemistry of the six members?)

2653
01:34:12,413 --> 01:34:14,813
(Watch it live!)

2654
01:34:15,013 --> 01:34:16,053
It must be cold.

2655
01:34:16,283 --> 01:34:19,453
(See you next week.)
